<HEAD>

<TITLE>VIA Kit Online: Tools: Hospitality Training</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<a href="../index.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"></a>

<a href="../via.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/visitor.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>

<a href="viakit.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/kit.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>
<p>
<a href="overview.htm">Overview</a> - 
<a href="resear.htm">Research</a> - 
<a href="resource.htm">Resources</a> - 
<a href="govt.htm">Government</a> - 
<a href="medi.htm">Media Relations</a> - 
<a href="tools.htm">Tools And Ideas</a>

<br><HR>

<H1>Hospitality Training</H1>

<H2>You know it when you see it . . . it's Customer Service!</H2>

<P>
The smile-the warm greeting-the attitude that says &quot;welcome.&quot;
 The willingness to help find answers, to solve problems.
<H2>Hospitality Training does make a difference to your business.
</H2>

<P>
Satisfied customers, repeat business, a healthy business climate
and a bright future for the visitor industry in Oregon-these are
the benefits that come from having a front-line workforce with
the skills, resources, and awareness to make the most of every
opportunity, every day.
<H2>What does the training involve?</H2>

<P>
&quot;We Put the <I>Oh!</I> In Oregon&quot; teaches &quot;what&quot;
to say and &quot;how&quot; to say it-the basics of good customer
service-giving your employees the resources they need to be effective
HOSTS for Oregon and your business.
<H2>It's easy to get started . . .</H2>

<P>
Contact your local chamber of commerce or visitor bureau to preview
the tape and to get in touch with a trainer in your area, or contact
the Oregon Tourism Alliance to get further assistance or to order
a video tape and training materials.
<H2>YES!  I would like to learn how to put the &quot;Oh!&quot;
in Oregon!</H2>

For more information or to order materials contact:  Oregon Tourism
Alliance
<br>
c/o Janet Porter, PO Box 20057, Keizer, Oregon 97307   (503) 393-3535, 
<a href="mailto: JanPorter@aol.com">JanPorter@aol.com</a>
<P>
Source: Oregon Tourism Alliance
<P>
