<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Mannatech - Nutraceutical Frontrunner</H1><BR><IMG SRC="/pics/Glyco.jpg"><BR><I><B>Cellular Communication:</B><BR></CENTER>The genetic information of the cell is stored in the DNA. It is then transferred to the RNA which is the duplicate blueprint required to express this information. This message is then put into the language of cell (glycoform) through the use of eight known saccharides. These glycoforms are then attached to proteins which create glycoproteins. Glycoproteins then penetrate the outer cell wall to enable the genetically coded information of that cell to be communicated to other cells.</I><BR><BR><BR>Those who do not know much about Mannatech Inc., had better get prepared! Mannatech, a three-year-old company located in Grand Prairie, Texas, has been patiently laying the groundwork to become a major player in the complementary health care industry that is exploding worldwide. The company's unprecedented commitment to research and development has propelled it years ahead of the nutritional pack and onto the same playing field shared by some of the world's largest pharmaceutical companies. All are developing patented technologies that meet the criteria for a new category of health care products.<BR>The focus is nutraceuticals, the new term used by the Food and Nutrition Board of the Institute of Medicine to describe functional food products with a proven relationship to health maintenance. Their potential for revolutionizing our attitudes toward nutrition and health has led companies worldwide on an all-out search for new functional food patents.<BR>While Mannatech has been quietly building an Associate base of over 150,000 and processing a monthly wholesale product sales volume exceeding $8 million, (as of September 1996), the company has been proactive in securing its position in an industry that Newsweek sees as the "next financial blockbuster." The launch of this industry is facilitated by two enormous factors: One is demand, the other legislation. <BR><BR><BR><H3>The Demand</H3>A recent article in The Journal of the American Medical Association (JAMA), estimated that 40% of Americans have turned away from the traditional use of drugs and are searching for alternative products to treat their medical problems. The reasons most often cited for this change were that drugs are (1) too toxic, (2) too expensive, and (3) too unreliable. A CBS story on the same subject estimated the number to be in the range of 50%.<BR>Based on this trend of taking responsibility for one's own health, Mannatech has established itself as the forerunner in an industry that provides products to help maintain optimal good health. Thus, the need for expensive, potentially toxic and sometimes unreliable drug therapy may be minimized before it even becomes necessary.<BR><BR><BR><H3>The Legislation</H3>In October of 1994, the President signed into law the Dietary Supplement Health and Education Act (DSHEA). As a manifestation of public opinion, this legislation demonstrates the trend for consumers to take responsibility for their own health maintenance programs.<BR>The DSHEA was written to empower American consumers to make choices about their own preventative healthcare programs so that the need for expensive drugs is minimized.<BR>In the DSHEA, Congress acknowledged that:<BR><BR>1) Science has linked good nutrition and the benefits of dietary supplements with health promotion and disease prevention;<BR><BR>2) Preventative health measures, including appropriate use of safe dietary supplements will decrease disease; and<BR><BR>3) Prevention of disease will reduce the country's health care expenses.<BR><BR>The commission on Dietary Supplement Labels, set up by the DSHEA, and the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) are currently working out specifics of how the law will be enforced. The original target date of late 1996 has been extended; and while the deadline for completing this enormous task remains uncertain, the industry is moving ahead and taking on a life of its own. This has created an environment in which Mannatech is solidifying its initial successes and preparing to move to the next levels in both products and business.<BR><BR><BR><H3>Big Bucks</H3>Providing access to natural, non-toxic health care products for the public has proven to be overwhelmingly successful in Europe where nutraceuticals have been marketed for several years. The JAMA issue of February 22, 1995, reported that in 1993 over $7 billion was spent on nutraceuticals in Germany alone. Nutraceutical regulation in Europe is the basis for much of the new U.S. legislation. <BR>As yet, we're only seeing the tip of the nutraceutical iceberg. The Chairman of the Foundation for Innovation in Medicine, Dr. Stephen DeFelice, estimates that 50% of the $503 billion spent on food products is used for nutraceutical purposes (Genetic Engineering, January 1, 1995, p. 40). The opportunities for nutraceuticals are absolutely unprecedented.<BR><BR><BR><H3>Who Benefits?</H3>The cost of conducting research for nutraceutical products doesn't approach the estimated $300 million expense in bringing a new drug to market, but is nevertheless substantial. In Europe, companies have found that the only reason to seek nutraceutical approval is to protect patent claims. Otherwise, the cost of nutraceutical approval for a food component available to anyone is unrealistically high. <BR>The key to profitability is in proprietary patents. JAMA reports that since nutraceuticals now sell as well as drugs in Europe and since the US market is poised to open, the world's largest pharmaceutical companies are buying every available functional component patent they can get their hands on which meets the criteria of a nutraceutical. A patent does not necessarily guarantee a product's standardization, efficacy, or safety; however, each of those unique substances that can qualify are worth their weight in gold in this new arena.<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><IMG SRC="/pics/Mole.jpg"><BR><I>A computer representation of Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT> complex.</I></CENTER><H3>Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT> Complex- Patented Cornerstone</H3>If carbohydrate technology is medicine's next frontier, then Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT> complex will take man to undreamed of places (see the article in this newspaper on Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT> complex). Developed and patented by Mannatech's scientific team, headed by Dr. Bill McAnalley, Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT> complex is what distinguishes Mannatech products and opportunity from the competition.<BR><BR><BR><H3>The Company</H3>Mannatech is a privately held company founded in 1993 which began operations in early 1994. Among its three primary stock holders is a strong, diverse assortment of skills and experience with which they support their key roles in company management. <BR>Responsibilities for international expansion and corporate finance fall under the direction of the Chairman of the Board, Skip Fioretti. A successful entrepreneur, Skip was the first Outback Steakhouse franchisee outside the state of Florida. When Outback went public in 1992, Skip was offered a substantial buyout for his multiple franchise units. Skip's financial and administrative track record aided Mannatech in securing its original licensing agreement with Carrington Laboratories for its patented aloe vera extract. <BR>Developing the marketing strategy and the compensation program was the responsibility of Mannatech President Sam Caster. Known nationally for his creative marketing concepts, Sam has brought companies in both direct sales and MLM from inception to annual sales exceeding $50 million and $100 million respectively. <BR>Utilizing his years of biotech experience, Bill Fioretti, Chief Science Officer, heads a scientific team that is second to none in carbohydrate technology and new product development. Together, Skip, Sam and Bill comprise the voting Board of Directors who will guide Mannatech as it becomes a major player in the international arena of nutraceutical technology.<BR><BR><BR><H3>The Bottom Line</H3>No one group of products has ever generated the level of enthusiastic endorsements coming from Mannatech's notable consumers. Endorsements from some of the world's top athletes, doctors, researchers, professional sports teams and business people regarding the products' effectiveness are on file. Compound this promotional bonanza with the unlimited potential of Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT>-based products in the nutraceutical market, and you have the opportunity of a lifetime. Many full-time Mannatech Associates are already generating significant incomes. Many more see the potential to position themselves to benefit from the ground level of this enormous opportunity. Mannatech has designed the most comprehensive, flexible, and lucrative compensation plan in network marketing. It provides opportunities to cash in on unlimited width and depth in an organization's sales as well as from the infinity bonuses on training programs. The entire program has been designed to position our part-time Associates for maximum success. Those who wish to go full-time immediately can also benefit from up-front sales commissions on entry packages. Professional network marketers agree; Mannatech has designed the most innovative bonus program in the entire industry. <BR>Yet, the power of the Mannatech opportunity lies in the Associates' ability to harness all the proprietary products' self-selling qualities simply by making a small monthly qualifying purchase. It makes the business simple, the results achievable, step by step. By design, none of the usual distractions, such as tracking group sales, keep Associates from their primary objective: introducing our products' effectiveness and the unlimited opportunity. The figures show that it works. Nowhere else is it possible to find such a substantial financial opportunity for both full- and part-time participants. <BR>By now, one point should be crystal clear: Mannatech is not just another nutritional MLM company trying to compete with a copycat product line. With patented, proprietary cutting-edge products and innovative compensation design, Mannatech has carefully plotted a strategy that could make it the next giant in this industry.<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
