<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Award for Top Biochemistry Discovery <BR>in 1996 Given to Texas Scientists</H1><BR><IMG SRC="/pics/Docs.jpg"><BR><I>From left to right: H. Reg McDaniel, MD and Bill McAnalley, PhD <BR>accept the ANMA award from Dr. Steve Nugent.</I><BR></CENTER><BR><BR><BR>The American Naturopathic Medical Association (ANMA) of Detroit, Michigan, has presented its highest scientific honor of recognition to Bill McAnalley, PhD, research pharmacologist, and H. Reg McDaniel, MD, pathologist. ANMA, the largest association for natural health care practitioners in the U.S., presented a plaque citing work of the research team (also including Eric Moore, DChem and William C. Fioretti, biochemist) for the development of the nutritional carbohydrate complex, Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT>, and the subsequent patent filing on this complex. The selection committee of the ANMA presents this award annually for the most significant progress made in biochemistry.<BR>Dr. McAnalley, in his acceptance response, explained that this patent protects the proprietary combination of the eight naturally derived saccharides used by mammalian cells to synthesize the molecules responsible for cell-to-cell communication. Of the 200+ saccharides occurring in nature, only these eight saccharides are known to be used by the body to synthesize glycoconjugates (glycoproteins and glycolipids). <BR>Dr. McDaniel stressed that, "The best medical therapy in the world will never be as effective as it could be without the support of good nutrition, which can be enhanced greatly with dietary supplements." He went on to explain that the  genes of animal cells that contain the operational instructions necessary to defend the body tissues need specific nutritional components to fulfill their genetic functions.<BR>In conclusion, Dr. McDaniel stated, "We are extremely excited about the potential of Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT> complex in support of good health, because it provides necessary glyco-nutritional components that support cellular communication."<BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
