<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Mannatech's Scientific Team</H1><BR><IMG SRC="/pics/Drs.jpg"><BR><I>Front row from left to right: <A HREF="EV.html">Eileen Vennum, RAC</A> and <A HREF="BM.html">Bill McAnalley, PhD</A>.<BR>Back Row from left to right: <A HREF="BW.html">Bob Ward, PED</A>; <A HREF="WF.html">William C. Fioretti</A>; <BR><A HREF="EM.html">Eric Moore, DChem</A> and <A HREF="RM.html">H. Reg McDaniel, MD</A>.</I><BR><H4>For short bios click on the name above.</H4><BR></CENTER><BR>In the high stakes game of nutraceuticals, Mannatech has drawn a "pat hand" with the scientific team it has assembled. No team in America has more experience in the discovery and utilization of carbohydrates, the organic compounds experts consider to be the next frontier in nutritional science. Harnessing the future of this infant industry can only be done by those with the ability to establish proprietary rights to these new discoveries. It's the arena in which members of Mannatech's scientific team have earned their spurs. They're responsible for the filing and receipt of over 65 patents for Carrington Laboratories worldwide.<BR>Coordinating the team is Mannatech co-founder and Chief Scientific Officer, William C. Fioretti, a biochemist with years of experience in product formulation. Bill's work on the standardization and use of plant sterols from the herb Dioscorea created national awareness of the health-building potential of prohormone (DHEA) precursors. That information made Mannatech PLUS and MVP two of the most copied products in the health food industry. <BR>Mannatech was finally able to distance itself from imitators when Bill discovered the enormous potential in combining plant sterols with certain carbohydrates. His work stemmed from discoveries by Bill McAnalley, Ph.D. and medical research by H. Reg McDaniel, M.D. concerning the uniquely structured mannan-linked carbohydrates from the aloe vera plant. Their work, which has generated global recognition, was begun at Carrington Laboratories.The core group of this team which first did research at Carrington Laboratories, including Dr. McDaniel, Dr. McAnalley and Dr. Eric Moore, has been reassembled at Mannatech. Their goal is to look beyond, from the immune-modulating capabilities of various carbohydrates to the unique nutritional value these carbohydrates provide to the body. From this work have come the latest and most significant patent claims: those for the nutritional use of the eight known monosaccharides required in the production of glycoconjugates. Trademarked Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT>, this proprietary carbohydrate complex is the cornerstone of Mannatech products and represents one of the most significant nutraceutical-grade discoveries to date. The American Naturopathic Medical Association recognized that fact with the association's annual award presented in 1996 to Dr. McAnalley and Dr. McDaniel for the most important progress in biochemistry.<BR>These achievements are just the beginning, the team reports. In the hands of this scientific powerhouse, the future is bright indeed. Enhancing this team of standouts are Eileen Vennum, RAC and Bob Ward, PED. Eileen, a Certified Regulatory Affairs Specialist, was brought on board to help Mannatech navigate the minefield of FDA regulations. Eileen's work is critical as the laws pertaining to the use and labeling of dietary supplements continue to evolve. <BR>Providing unique insight into the role nutraceuticals can play in fitness and athletics is Dr. Bob Ward. Conditioning coach and sports scientist for the Dallas Cowboys Football Club for 14 years, Dr. Ward is also the co-author of the Encyclopedia of Biomechanics. His knowledge and experience bring together a unique blend of pure and applied research that draws upon the fields of biomechanics, exercise physiology, information processing, computer prescription technology, martial arts skills and conditioning program technology for application in the emerging field of human performance measurement and assessment.<BR>Clearly, this is a pre-eminent team of experts which makes Mannatech the unquestioned leader in the field of nutraceuticals and positions the company for prominent involvement in the emergent disciplines of prevention and wellness.<BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
