<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>TEXAS BUSINESS<BR>Profiles Mannatech</H1><BR><IMG SRC="/pics/TxBs.jpg"><BR><BR><I>September 1996/by Joe Grey</I><BR><BR></CENTER>"Some of America's biggest companies, including MCI and Amway, are convinced that MLM is about to enjoy a breakthrough in public awareness in much the same way franchising did in the '70s. In preparation for that day, and to maximize MLM's potential, some companies have tried big royalty payouts, celebrity endorsers, elaborate promotional materials, and even high-pressure pitches to employ distributors and generate revenue. Grand Prairie-based Mannatech Inc. is trying an unusual tactic that perhaps should not be so unusual: letting the product sell itself...After all, MLM is all about word-of-mouth: The message of one distributor motivates another person to go out and become a distributor... fueled solely by the quality and popularity of the product; no one is going to personally tout a product they feel is a dud.<BR>"This is central to why Mannatech decided to market its products through multilevel distributors: they are convinced their products have the level of quality needed to generate a significant buzz in the industryÉ<BR>"'As a physician, I've seen every kind of hype imaginable,' says Maurice Stevens, M.D. and Mannatech distributor. 'I am not stretching the truth when I talk about the amazing results I've seen from the products. In fact, I actually have to restrain myself because it sounds so unbelievable. The bottom line is: these products work.' Leroy Burrell, one-time world record holder in the 100-meter dash and '96 Olympian, credits Mannatech products as a very important part of improving training times and recovery from hard workouts.' Mike Marsh, 1992 Olympic gold-medalist in the 200 meters, says: 'Mannatech's products have improved my workouts, my recovery, and my performance. I believe they will give me the edge I need to bring home the gold again.' Mannatech has a veritable Who's Who list of athletes (none of whom are paid) singing endorsement-like praise. The company also boasts more than 130,000 distributors throughout the U.S. and Canada and $7 million in monthly sales.<BR><BR><B>But why MLM?</B><BR>Mannatech's incredible growth can be credited entirely to multi-level marketing, a method that admittedly makes some people cringe and others falsely suspect the product's credibility. Many still wonder: Can a MLM company be legitimate in the food supplement industry? Is there such a thing?<BR>"'If you would have asked me that question five years ago,' Dr. Bucci says, 'I would have said no. I would have bashed them. But they've really cleaned up their act. Some of the best supplements are sold by multi-level marketing companies. The reason is they educate consumers better than anyone.' Education, of course, is why multi-level marketing is a necessary choice for many companies; their products can have little impact on the market unless the customer has a clear understanding of what they do and how they operate.<BR>Mannatech credits its striking sales performance to properly educating consumers. The education affords Mannatech one other crucial benefit: it helps consumers understand why their products are in a class of their own."Mannatech announced August 9 that it has taken a step in securing a proprietary position in the rapidly changing health care industry with the filing of a new set of patent claims for their recently trademarked complex called Ambrotose<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT> complex."<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
