petitive Swimming</H2><H3>Purpose</H3>The purpose of the study was to determine the measurable benefits of Mannatech products on swimmers after 12 weeks of intensive training. <BR><BR><BR><H3>Research Team</H3>Bill Jewell, Head Swim Coach, with his assistants, Ken Hamdorf, Steve Bentley, Study Director, and Bob Ward, Research Consultant with Mannatech, contributed to the implementation of the study. Study Director, Steve Bentley, compiled and analyzed the swimming data.<BR><BR><BR><H3>Golden West Swimming Program - <BR>Background/History</H3>Golden West College's swim record is superlative. Behind every good program, however, is outstanding leadership. That's just what Head Swim Coach, Bill Jewell, provides. Bill will be the first to tell you that being successful requires the right mix of talent, coaching, scientific training programs, and of course, the good luck generated by hard work. <BR>For some teams, winning one state meet would be enough to validate the program's efficacy. However, Golden West College has gone significantly beyond that achievement, exceeding the laws of probability for winning over the last 25 years. Golden West teams have been Conference Champions 22 out of the last 25 years; California State Champions in 1985, '86, '90 and '95. Golden West teams were runners-up in 1983, '91, '92 and '94. It would be safe to say that men's swimming and water polo are strongly emphasized at Golden West College. The 17-member swim team has swimmers from California, Oregon, Washington, Wyoming, Hawaii, Mexico, Sweden and Switzerland, an indication that the program's reputation extends far beyond the California border.<BR><BR><BR><H4>Objectives:</H4>Does the use of Mannatech products:<BR>A. Enhance performance<BR>B. Improve endurance<BR><BR><BR><H4>Subjects:</H4>17 male swimmers were eligible for the study, ranging from 18 to 21 years of age. All of the swimmers had trained intensely for the 12 weeks prior to the study and were in peak condition.<BR><BR><BR><H4>Groups:</H4>All 17 swimmers were given the option of taking the Mannatech products. 12 swimmers opted to try the products. Five opted not to try them. That presented the opportunity to break the team into two groups. The Test Group consisted of 12 swimmers: four Distance Swimmers, three Middle Distance Swimmers, five Sprinters. The Control Group of five swimmers included one Distance Swimmer and four Middle Distance Swimmers.<BR><BR><BR><H4>Length of Study:</H4>The study was 22 days in length, starting on April 13, 1996, and concluding May 4, 1996. It included the most important meets on the swim team calendar: The Golden West Invitational, April 13; The Conference Champion-ships, April 26-27; The State Champion-ship Meet, May 2-4.<BR><BR><BR><H4>Training During the Study:</H4>All swimmers trained the same amount of time per week. Intensity of the training sessions were varied according to the events swum. Training sessions included one hour swimming, a.m., five days per week; two hours swimming, p.m. six days per week; one hour of weights three days per week.<BR><BR><BR><H4>Mannatech Products Used:</H4>The following Mannatech products were used each day:<BR>1). Man&#183;Aloe&#174;: six capsules per day-two capsules each, a.m., noon, bedtime;<BR>2). SPORT: five capsules per day-two after a.m. workout, three after p.m. workout;<BR>3). EM&#183;PACT<FONT SIZE=-3>(TM)</FONT>: one packet with ten oz. water-one serving 20 to 30 minutes before workout or events.<BR><BR><BR><H4>Improvements Measured Against Two Standards:</H4>1. Time improvements against lifetime best times.<BR>2. Time improvements against season's unrested best times.<BR><BR><BR><BR><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLSPACING=2 ><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TH WIDTH=300><BR><H2>Lifetime Best Times vs.<BR>        1996 Best Times</H2></TH></TR><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TD><BR>Test Group = 0.71 seconds/100 yd. drop<BR><BR>              Control Group = 0.32 seconds/100 yd. drop<BR></TD></TR><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TD><BR><B>NOTE:<BR>              Season-to-season expected value =<BR>              0.40 seconds/100 yds.</B><BR></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><BR><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLSPACING=2 ><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TH WIDTH=300><BR><H2>1996 Tired Best Times vs.<BR>        1996 Rested Best Times</H2></TH></TR><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TD><BR>Test Group = 2.40 seconds/100 yd. drop<BR><BR>              Control Group = 1.90 seconds/100 yd. drop<BR></TD></TR><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TD><BR><B>NOTE:<BR>              Season unrested best times =<BR>              2.0 seconds/100 yds.</B><BR></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><BR><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLSPACING=2 ><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TH WIDTH=300><BR><H2>Final Reuslts</H2>        GOLDEN WEST COLLEGE</TH></TR><TR ALIGN=CENTER>    <TD><BR><B>1996 State Champions<BR><BR>              Set a scoring record:<BR>               758.5 points earned<BR><BR>                Won 10 of 18 events<BR><BR>                Swam 38 individual<BR>                All-American races</B><BR>               </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
