S. Olympic Team which did not compete in the games due to the U.S. boycott.<BR>Any girl who's wanted to compete with the boys can envy Nancy. She's appeared in the Utah Jazz Summer League and in Spud Webb's All-Star Game where she competed with such high-profile guys as Magic Johnson and Isiah Thomas and has gone one-on-one with Michael Johnson.<BR><BR><CENTER><IMG SRC="/pics/NanHF.jpg"><BR><BR><I>1996 NBA Hall of Fame inductees from left to right: <BR>George Gervin, Gail Goodrich, Nancy Lieberman-Cline, David Thompson, George Yardley</I><BR><BR><BR></CENTER>Her talents extend well beyond the basketball court. Nancy is recognized as the driving force behind Martina Navratilova's rise to the pinnacle of women's tennis. As Martina's conditioning coach, Nancy developed strategies and methods that revolutionized the way women train. She was the first female named to President Reagan's "Sports Drug Awareness Program." As a part of Governor Mario Cuomo's Anti-Drug Student Leadership Program, Nancy has helped educate youngsters about the hazards of drug and alcohol use.<BR><BR><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 SRC="/pics/NanF.jpg">She's an accomplished broadcaster, a popular keynote speaker whose regular audiences include members of the Fortune 500, the owner of a sports marketing company: Events Marketing Inc., and she also conducts basketball camps for several weeks each year. She serves on the boards of the Women's Sports Foundation, and Nebraska Sports Magazine, also contributing time and effort to the Juvenile Diabetes Foundation, Special Olympics, and Boys' and Girls' clubs, among others. On top of all this, she relishes her role as the wife of Tim Cline and mother of two-year-old Timothy Joseph Cline Jr., called TJ. Whew! The traveling squad and the Terrible Two's?<BR>How does she do it? She's sneaking up on age 40, but it's not at all apparent. In fact, Nancy could have originated the "I'm not getting older, I'm getting better" phrase. Last spring, a reporter for the "L.A. Times" asked Nancy how she expected to keep up with the young women in their twenties who would be her Women's NBA teammates and opponents next year. "At the time," Nancy says, "I acknowledged that I probably wouldn't have the endurance to play more than half a game, 18 - 20 minutes, of quality basketball. Since I've been taking the Mannatech products, I've found that I'm able to play a full 40 minutes of high-quality ball. I talked to the same reporter recently and told him that I was retracting that estimate and I told him why. Do you know what he said? He said, 'I'm shocked!' I had to laugh. I'm shocked, too! This is totally unexpected." When her teammates quiz Nancy about her surprising endurance and lack of muscle soreness, she shares information on Mannatech products with them, especially EM&#183;PACT and SPORT. Nancy says, "The older you get, the more you need an edge. Mannatech products give me that edge. This is an arena where every percentage point of difference counts. When something can give you even a 1% edge - and I know I gain much more than that - it makes the difference between being just a good player and being a star. Mannatech makes the difference. I love this company!"<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><I>Reproduction of athlete and celebrity endorsements is strictly prohibited.<BR>Athletic performance was achieved through the combination of exercise, <BR>good diet and nutritional supplementation. Results will vary with individuals.</I></CENTER><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
