<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Tony Volpentest</H1><H3>The world's fastest amputee athlete</H3><BR><IMG SRC="/pics/TV1.jpg"><BR><BR></CENTER><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=10 SRC="/pics/TV2.jpg">Through Mannatech's advanced nutritional technology, some of the world's top professional and amateur athletes have reported enhanced performance and recovery. Probably the most extraordinary of these athletes is Tony Volpentest.Tony is classified as the fastest amputee athlete in the world. In the 1992 Paralympics in Barcelona, he won two gold medals and set world records in the 100 and 200 meter races. He is also the U.S. record holder for the 100 and 200 meter races. He was the Everett Herald Man of the Year in Sports in 1991. He was "Sports Illustrated" Athlete of the Month and first runner-up for Athlete of the Year in 1993, and received the Franklin Delano Roosevelt Award for the Physically Challenged for 1994.<BR>The youngest of six children, Tony was born without wrists, ankles, hands or feet. His legs and arms were only partially formed. That made no difference to his family who always encouraged him to be as active as other children. He grew up with the idea that he could do anything, and his accomplishments prove him right. Running on specially designed spring-release prostheses, Tony has achieved speeds that are impressive by any standards.<BR>In 1995, Tony was introduced to Mannatech products. After being on the products for just three weeks, he stated, "My workouts now are absolutely phenomenal! Every day I go to training thinking there is no way I can top what I did yesterday, but when I leave at 4:30, I tell my coach I had another great workout." Tony said he especially likes SPORT and PLUS because he believes the products help him recover quickly from his intense workouts.<BR><BR><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 SRC="/pics/TV3.jpg">In Barcelona in 1992, Tony set the previous world's record in the 100 meters: 11.63 seconds, a time he thought unbeatable. At the 1996 Paralympics in Atlanta, after having trained for the last year on SPORT and PLUS, Tony set a new world record of 11.36 in the 100 meters and won another gold in the 200 with a time of 23.28. Tony says emphatically, "I feel that these products definitely give me an edge on my competition. Mannatech is great." <BR>Now that the games are over, Tony has determined his next goal. "I plan on building my Mannatech business and sharing these great products with people everywhere," he said. "I couldn't be more excited about my future with Mannatech." When he speaks at a Mannatech event, Tony always attracts large audiences. This young man is a remarkable athlete and an even more outstanding, inspirational role model for people of all ages.<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><I>Reproduction of athlete and celebrity endorsements is strictly prohibited.<BR>Athletic performance was achieved through the combination of exercise, <BR>good diet and nutritional supplementation. Results will vary with individuals.</I></CENTER><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
