<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>4 smart reasons to build<BR>with the All-Star Business Pack</H1><I>by David Colister</I><BR><BR></CENTER>The visual differences between 24-karat gold and look-alike metals can be subtle to the untrained eye. The difference in how people treat them, however, is not at all subtle. Our opportunity has already proven to be as good as gold to those who have the proper tools, training, work ethic, attitude and business plan in place. I have found that success in Mannatech is really not as much about talent as it is common sense. Some people simply treat this business like a business-not a game or a hobby-a business. These business types seem to go so much faster than the rest. Personally, I had to decide why I was involved-to have another hobby or to get wealthy. Once I was sure I wanted wealth and stopped tinkering, my organization absolutely exploded. The quick growth almost seemed too easy. The difference was all in how I perceived and treated my opportunity.<BR><BR>Chris Parker, a close friend from Cleveland and one of my best trainers, said to me, "David, it seems there are three kinds of people who get into Mannatech: those who get in only to buy the products at wholesale, those who treat Mannatech like a hobby, and those who understand the true potential of the opportunity and run their businesses like the multi-million-dollar money-maker it really is. Only the latter see their businesses take off and prosper." <BR><BR>Bullseye! From my vantage point as former Mannatech Vice President Marketing and Communications and now as a full-time Associate, I couldn't agree more. I especially like the difference Chris distinguishes between the hobbiest and business person. It identifies that "certain something" that separates those who get wealthy and those who only watch others get that way. First, let me say there are many legitimate strategies for building a successful Mannatech organization. However, after Sam Caster checked the computers and delved deep into business-building strategy, he discovered that the quickest way to build a lucrative business is by enrolling people through the All-Star Business Pack and concentrating on the Corporate Training Bonuses. Here are only four reasons why:<BR><BR><B>Reason 1.</B><BR>If you sign up with the $1000 All-Star Business Pack (ASBP), it only takes enrolling five other ASBPs to get your investment back, whereas if you sign up as a Master Associate (MA) for $229, it takes ten MA enrollees to fully recoup your investment. The ASBP approach is 200% more effective at returning the initial capital investment. If someone is tight on money, help them go for ASBP sign-ups and get them their investment capital with only five sponsored instead of ten.<BR><BR><B>Reason 2.</B><BR>It only takes enrolling five ASBPs to make $1,000, whereas it takes 40 MAs or 100 $49 enrollees to make $1,000. The ASBP approach is 800% faster than the MA approach and 10,000% faster than the "Consumer Associate" ($49 enrollment) approach in helping people make substantial amounts of money quickly. Remember, it's not just how much is made, but how quickly the Associate makes it that determines how soon an Associate is able to make Mannatech a full-time business. <BR><BR><B>Reason 3.</B><BR>If someone enrolls at the Consumer Associate (CA) level or MA level and their business really takes off (maybe several ASBP sign-ups or a lot of volume), they will lose all binary volume that would have been placed in all the other income centers because they did not have the personal wholesale volume necessary ($600) to qualify all their income centers. The CA and MA enrollees only have their number one income center qualified. If it takes them two to three months (or more) to qualify all their income centers, it could feasibly cost them much more than the initial investment difference between the CA or MA levels and the ASBP. In reality, it could cost them thousands of dollars. The ASBP approach is the most practical enrollment approach for those who are serious about making all the money they work for.<BR><BR><B>Reason 4.</B><BR>If someone enrolls at the CA level and others in their organization enroll through the ASBP, they won't get credit for them in their training bonuses, which could cost them a tremendous amount of money. Don't let anybody in your organization enroll for training before you or you will lose out on the most lucrative revenue stream in our compensation plan.If you want to attract business professionals into your organization, you are going to have to show them, in real terms, how to replace their current income very quickly. These types are very busy and don't generally have one to three years to "play" at making money. If you don't present a plan that helps them generate immediate and sizable income, you could soon lose them. Showing only income from the ASBP approach five-wide and four levels deep* will stimulate the entrepreneurial blood of just about any serious business or corporate person. If showing an annual income of $100,000 doesn't stir them because it is too small, just take the plan a couple of levels deeper to reflect the Leadership bonuses which will take them into a seven-figure income. Warning: don't show the high numbers too soon with people who have never made a six-figure income. Although the incomes are very real, it usually goes way beyond that which is believable. <BR>In a few years, several Mannatech Associates will be earning mid-seven-figure incomes. By building your business with All-Star Business Packs, maybe you'll be one of them. "There's gold in them there pills!"<BR>For a full explanation of the which pack might be the perfect fit for you, call Visua.com toll-free at 888.478.2266 to get a copy of David Colister's audio cassette, "Where Do I Go From Here?" If you're already convinced that a career with Mannatech is best for you and wish to maximize your business-building potential, order a copy of David's two-tape, advanced training audio set entitled, "Selling the $1,000 Pack."<BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
