<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Mannatech's Scientific Team</H1><BR><IMG SRC="/pics/Drs.jpg"><BR><I>Front row from left to right: <A HREF="EV.html">Eileen Vennum, RAC</A> and <A HREF="BM.html">Bill McAnalley, PhD</A>.<BR>Back Row from left to right: <A HREF="BW.html">Bob Ward, PED</A>; <A HREF="WF.html">William C. Fioretti</A>; <BR><A HREF="EM.html">Eric Moore, DChem</A> and <A HREF="RM.html">H. Reg McDaniel, MD</A>.</I><BR><H4>For short bios click on the name above.</H4><BR></CENTER><BR><CENTER><H2>Eileen Vennum, RAC (Regulatory Affairs Certified)</H2></CENTER>A native of Baton Rouge, Louisiana, Eileen attended David Lipscomb College in Nashville and Harding University in Searcy, Arkansas. As Director of R&D Regulatory Affairs, she spent six years at Carrington Laboratories working in Research and Development with Dr. Bill McAnalley and Dr. Eric Moore.  <BR>Certified as a Regulatory Affairs Professional by the Regulatory Affairs Professional Society, her experience includes a broad range of interactions with the Food and Drug Administration (FDA), with an emphasis on activities that support new product development. She has extensive experience working as liaison between industry and District Offices of the FDA, with several divisions of the FDA in new drug development, and with the FDA Center for Devices and Radiological Health in development of medical devices. Ms. Vennum has filed and maintained several successful investigational new drug applications (INDs), and several successful 510(k) notifications for medical devices. <BR>Ms. Vennum's experience also includes registration of medical devices for export to foreign countries, handling FDA inspections, developing and labeling products containing OTC monographed drugs, training pharmaceutical employees in regulatory issues applicable to their jobs, and developing systems for standard operating procedures. Ms. Vennum's experience includes development of pharmaceutical R&D Document Control systems that conform to regulatory requirements for maintenance of records in all areas of drug and device development, manufacturing and marketing.<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
