<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Mannatech's Scientific Team</H1><BR><IMG SRC="/pics/Drs.jpg"><BR><I>Front row from left to right: <A HREF="EV.html">Eileen Vennum, RAC</A> and <A HREF="BM.html">Bill McAnalley, PhD</A>.<BR>Back Row from left to right: <A HREF="BW.html">Bob Ward, PED</A>; <A HREF="WF.html">William C. Fioretti</A>; <BR><A HREF="EM.html">Eric Moore, DChem</A> and <A HREF="RM.html">H. Reg McDaniel, MD</A>.</I><BR><H4>For short bios click on the name above.</H4><BR></CENTER><BR><CENTER><H2>Eric Moore, PhD</H2></CENTER>Eric Moore was born in Dallas, Texas and spent part of his childhood in the Dallas area before he moved to San Francisco, Salt Lake City, and finally, Arlington, Virginia. <BR>He then returned to Texas where he graduated in 1978 from the University of Texas at Austin with a B.A. degree in biochemistry. He did graduate work at the University of Texas at Dallas receiving a Master's degree in 1983 while working on a glycobiology project - the structure of a plant lectin, Concanavalin A, in solution by nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy (NMR). He completed his doctorate, also at the University of Texas at Dallas, in 1985 in physical organic chemistry. As a graduate student, he served an internship at Anderson-Clayton Foods (now part of Kraft) where his work was concentrated in the area of stabilizing fats for frying.<BR>In 1985, Eric began working with Dr. Bill McAnalley at Avacare, characterizing the active ingredients in aloe vera. This research eventually led to the patent filings for acemannan and Manapol&#174; powder. Later, as Director of Quality Assurance at Carrington Laboratories from 1987 to 1995, Eric produced the first batch of Manapol&#174; powder in Costa Rica in March 1993.<BR>Eric is listed on numerous patents and has authored a number of articles for publication.<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
