<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Business Professionals <BR>Choose Network Marketing</H1><BR></CENTER><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 SRC="/pics/Han.jpg"></A><H2>Gayle and John Hannett</H2>They gave themselves a year to reach All-Star Presidential, but they couldn't help it. Their Mannatech business grew so fast, they reached their goal in nine months! Unstoppable momentum? That's what Gayle and John will tell you.Gayle, the oldest of 12 children of a dentist, started helping in her dad's office when she was 12 years old. "It was a relief to get out of the house!" she reports. She became a dental hygienist and spent 15 years working for her father and set a precedent. All her brothers became dentists; her sisters all became hygienists.<BR>As her interest in the delivery of good health care grew, she formed a health care consulting firm with a dentist. Together they taught team-building workshops and gave seminars for dental teams where they helped office staffs become productive units much like families. One point Gayle specifically makes is that early on she began helping dentists create an office environment where patients saw themselves as clients and where they learned to take responsibility for themselves. That philosophy has really transferred, she says. Network marketing provides the best possible arena to do this.<BR>Gayle's first network marketing experience in 1989 taught her that the business works. She had wanted to get away from so much business travel. The home-based aspect and the residual income were what she was looking for. The checks, however, didn't represent the effort she was putting in. "When I met Ray Robbins," she reports, "he said, 'You can make much more than that in Mannatech.' He was right! When we went to Orlando and began to grasp the scope of this, we said, 'We can't NOT do this!'"<BR>"This gives us the opportunity to live based on our values," John said. A graduate of Albion College, he coached basketball, taught biology and was athletic director at a private school before earning his real estate license. "Real estate was a good fit for me," he says. "I'm big on listening. I teach my people to stop regurgitating all over everyone! That's because most sales are lost when people talk too much." He's demonstrated that the philosophy works. His real estate business is doing $100 million a year in sales.<BR>"I've always liked the network marketing concept," he went on. "Many people see the potential, but don't have the right opportunity. In Mannatech, it's a real opportunity to own and run your own business. You should invest yourself emotionally, intellectually, physically to that degree. Unlike other careers and professions where you're only as good as your last sale or operation or performance, Mannatech allows you to build and expand on every success. This is a Win/Win/Win situation."<BR>"There's so much power here", Gayle said, "in the products, in the people, in the company. They have our highest respect. These are unique products. This is a unique company. It's life-changing!"<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
