<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Business Professionals <BR>Choose Network Marketing</H1><BR></CENTER><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 SRC="/pics/Pete.jpg"></A><H2>Pete Laurence</H2>What's the synonym for "discipline"? Can you say, Pete Laurence? Paradise Valley's own one-time pig farmer/commercial pilot/ consumer electronic guru. Pete's success comes from two critical character traits: old-fashioned determination and self-discipline. Results? Four-Star Mannatech Associate in 30 days.<BR>A native New Yorker, raised in southern California, with an Animal Science degree from Cal State Poly, he developed a commercial hog operation in Chino Valley, Arizona, becoming the state's biggest pig farmer. At 6'6" and 275 pounds, he clearly took the prize.<BR>A severe winter decimated Pete's herd. His livelihood in shambles, he worked odd jobs, and reluctantly accepted a friend's offer to sell cars at his dealership. "I don't know how to sell and I don't like people," Pete told him. With a promise of training and a desire to be clean, he took the job. Training? Locked in a room with tapes on salesmanship, he couldn't come out until he showed he could succeed. Of course he did! Pete loves a challenge.<BR>Then, trading a pig for ground school and basic flight instruction, he moved to Florida. In just four and a half months, he was certified as a Flight Instructor and commercial, multi-engine, instrument-rated pilot.<BR>Alert for new opportunities, Pete has also created and operated a chain of consumer electronics stores and dabbled in commercial real estate sales and development.<BR>"I've learned from everything I've done," Pete explains, "Pig business: economies of scale; flying airplanes; the value of personality-free systems; sales; the importance of communication skills." Blending these, he founded Visioneering Productions, a sales training and business development firm where he put his broadly diverse background to work helping others.<BR>Almost ten years ago, he first looked at network marketing. A friend asked him to evaluate an MLM opportunity. Pete said, "I think you're crazy even to consider such a thing!" However, the business intrigued him. He analyzed industry and company and decided to get involved. Other business interrupted his budding career. Today he regrets going inactive because some of those who started when Pete started and persisted are multimillionaires today!<BR>Eventually, he returned to network marketing, enjoying significant financial success although several bad experiences convinced him that it wasn't the right choice for him. When Gayle Hannet wanted him to look at Mannatech, Pete wasn't interested. Gayle persisted, introducing him to Ray Robbins. After consideration, Pete called Ray for more information, not expecting the successful millionaire to return his call immediately. Imagine his surprise when Ray called back at 11 p.m.!<BR>Still, Pete was cautious. "I really did my due diligence," he says. Auditing Master Associate Training, he was impressed both by Associates and by their enthusiasm for the products. "They weren't the typically greedy, scheming, graspy people MLM often brings to mind," he says. "It felt right. I signed up the next day, went to Dallas for the next All-Star Training and requested a place at the first Trainers' Certification training.<BR>"For very personal reasons, I set a goal to be Four-Star in 30 days and I did it! If you care sincerely about your friends and loved ones, you can't help sharing Mannatech products; they're just too important. As you share, the information/product-purchase/results sequence will generate money. Even if money's not your primary goal the company will send it to you anyway."To those who say, 'I don't know how to do that,' I explain, 'You can learn. No one was born a pig farmer or a bank president. Every professional learned his/her skills. With Mannatech's great training programs and learning materials, anyone who chooses to be successful can be!'<BR>"Once you fully understand Mannatech, it's so sensible, it's inspirational. The company's well capitalized and profitable. It has skilled management well grounded in business and the subtleties of network marketing."Mannatech's compensation plan is obviously the best in the industry, combining the best features of every other successful plan. It creates a career track where even new, inexperienced, part-time people can enjoy financial success immediately.<BR>"Mannatech's product line is the real key. Its proven effectiveness answers the most important question in business analysis; Would people continue to buy these products, even without income potential attached to the purchase?"Mannatech's richness transcends financial wealth. It's given me a greater feeling of stability and security than I've ever had. I'm more mellow and relaxed, more accepting. I have a great degree of positive expectancy. The more I share Mannatech with others, the better I feel. Old friends have said, 'Bless you for sharing the product.' New acquaintances thank me for 'finally showing me a networking program that works.'<BR>"Don't let anyone tell you that he or she can't do this. If a pig farmer can do it..."<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
