<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Business Professionals <BR>Choose Network Marketing</H1><BR></CENTER><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 SRC="/pics/GM.jpg"></A><H2>Gail Hoag and Marian Head</H2>There are dynamic duos and then there are dynamic duos-Gail Hoag and Marian Head, for example. Their long-time friendship started as freshmen at the University of Maryland, has blossomed into a dynamic business in a field they never considered; network marketing! They bring some unique skills to this business.<BR>A serious student, Marian Head always focused on career. With a graduate degree in Educational Technology, she worked with the U.S. Senate for nine years and taught at the university level. "I thought Gail was crazy when she left her job," she says. "I was so fulfilled working in an organization. The first right brain thing I ever did was learn T'ai Chi. On my way to a workshop, I arranged a layover in San Francisco to see our friend, Marion Culhane. I mentioned some health problems I was having and she gave me some Mannatech products to try. I took them back to Boulder and told Gail about them. I could see that they had a beneficial effect on me, but not until Marion mentioned how much she was earning every month did it occur to either of us to turn this into a business. We were thinking on the consumer level. Completely unaccustomed to thinking of network marketing as serious business, we thought, 'This is a joke! What are we doing?'"<BR>What they're doing is moving past pre-defined paths. After the U. of Maryland, Gail attended the Corcoran School of Art, toured with a famous artist, practiced fine art and supported herself as a commercial artist. Moving to Boulder, she looked for something that would allow her to combine artistic expression with people, and found her niche in training and consulting. As rewarding as it was, there were also frustrations. Just three weeks after a successful team-building workshop she conducted for a major client, the company moved to consolidate and half her class received pink slips. "This is no fun," she thought, "I need to find something else."<BR>It was then that Marion Culhane offered them the Mannatech opportunity. When Gail and Marian realized what a superb business opportunity it was, they invested their considerable energies into making it a success. "Much of what we're doing in Mannatech," Marian says, "is what we were doing in corporate America."<BR>"We both realized that, unlike corporate America, there was no ceiling here," Gail says. "it's the most extraordinary personal development workshop I've ever been in. We've both learned a lot about perspective, about how you look at your business. Hobbyists and serious business builders look at this from completely different viewpoints. When we made an internal shift and began seeing it as a business, we learned to look for leaders instead of trying to share it with the whole world. Things really began to click. We committed to learn and grow, to change and keep going."<BR>"Originally, we committed for one year. We've already renewed that for four years! Marian says. "Richard Howard asked us in Orlando when we would be Presidential. We thought about it and said, 'By Seattle' Then we realized that was a lot of business- building to do if we were going to get there! Thank goodness for Marion Culhane! She's a great coach. She steps me through a sequence that really works for me, going from intention to reaction.' Claim the intention,' she says. 'Remove the limiting beliefs and let all the reactions come up to the intention.'"<BR>Obviously it works! Honored as Four-Star Presidential Associates, inducted into the Ring of Honor at Mannatech's Fall meeting in Bellevue, WA, Marian and Gail are now part of a team working on training materials that will be the envy of the industry.<BR>But when has the industry seen a partnership like this? A twosome that produces some serious business-building statistics and relishes every single minute of it!<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
