<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H1>Business Professionals <BR>Choose Network Marketing</H1><BR></CENTER><IMG ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10 SRC="/pics/Hav.jpg"></A><H2>Dwight and Susan Havener</H2>Dwight and Sue are "go-getters" to the core. Strong, goal-oriented, self-motivated, and hard-working are only a few of the qualities that make them such a great Mannatech success story. In the last ten months since they have been with us they have made over $225,000 and their income is just plain skyrocketing.<BR>Dwight grew up in the piano, organ, and keyboard retail business. His family owns 17 outlets and is very successful. Dwight, a concert jazz pianist, spent a lot of time as the front man for the stores-playing and speaking at mall and new store openings. He was just about to buy out the family business and fully lock himself into that industry when a strange phenomenon occurred with his perspective on business. His wife Susan was steadily making about $10,000 a month with another network marketing company for a number of years, and he began to envy her lifestyle. In the morning as they would kiss good-bye, he would leave home for work in a business suit, and she would leave for the beach in her bathing suit. They both worked hard when they worked, but she could take a cellular phone with her to the beach and do her business and her time always seemed to be her own. He, on the other hand, was required to march to the beat of a different drum, one that was pounded on by the dictates of the retail industry's hours and "corporate image" standards. Though the money looked good on both sides of the business fence, the lifestyle was definitely better on Susan's side. <BR>As a result of his increased interest in MLM they hired a $200-an-hour MLM consultant to evaluate their financial prospects as a team in networking. Dwight was considering not buying the family business (the bird in the hand) and going after MLM full-time. After the consultant reviewed Susan's (former) MLM company, their combined business style and talent mix, he informed them that they would never make their goal of one million dollars a year through Susan's company. She had been very successful, but her income had flattened out at $10,000 a month. He suggested that it would never get much higher, even if they both worked it.<BR>That led into phase two of the consultant's task: finding a company that would provide them that million-dollar-a-year opportunity. The guidelines were very rigid. The ideal company for them would: <BR><BR>1) Possess a genuine ground-floor opportunity, meaning that it was no more than a few years old and was not already doing more than $100,000,000 a year in sales;<BR><BR>2) Have products that would produce high resale demand because the emotional and/or physical experience necessitated the consumer's unwavering consumption or use;<BR><BR>3) Represent, in their products, cutting-edge technology that was brand new to the marketplace, and if possible, would have exclusive marketing rights to that technology;<BR><BR>4) Savvy management at the corporate level in creative marketing, technological breakthrough development, and business operations;<BR><BR>5) Be just beyond "infant" stage in business development and had a sufficient amount of growth momentum already in place;<BR><BR>6) Have "deep pocket" or, in other words, sufficient reserve capital to take advantage of any bright new opportunities or fix any major "bumps in their road;"<BR><BR>7) Have a large number of people who are not "professional" network marketers (people who had a pre-existing downline before entering the business) making substantial amounts of money.<BR><BR>Over 100 companies were carefully researched and Mannatech was the company the consultant recommended. "The biggest deciding factor for me," said Dwight, "was that Mannatech already had people making $30,000 a month who had never had any success in MLM before...I knew we had found our 'goose that lays the golden eggs...'" Sam Caster remembers how strictly the Haveners scrutinized and investigated the company, "Man! They asked all the tough questions...I knew these people meant business!"<BR>Dwight and Susan are dedicated and focused individuals in everything they do, from network marketing to Dwight's passion for triathlon competitions. They came from out of nowhere and put Florida on the Mannatech map. In eight months, they were already making over $30,000 a month. They train their people thoroughly for success and are seeing their people hit the big 5-figure monthly incomes right along with them. "Our goal was to be making $50,000 a month at the end of our first year and an annual income of $1,000,000 in our second year. Thanks to God and our wonderful people we are on track!"The goal that drives them more than any other is to produce at least 100 millionaires in their organization within their first five years in business. Folks, if you have never seen MLM legends in the making, the Haveners are a couple to watch. With their drive and commitment to the success of the people in their organization they are sure to be among Mannatech's biggest money earners for years to come.<BR>Dwight and Susan, thanks for bringing your energy and focus to the Mannatech family. We love you, and we love the example you are setting for all of us who want to maximize the potential of this great opportunity. Enjoy!<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
