</DOCHDR>
<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H2>The Efficacy and Safety of the Mannatech Optimal Health Plan</H2><BR><I><A HREF="Kaats.html">Back to Optimal Health Plan</A></I><BR><BR></center>If there's one thing on which Mannatech is focused, it's the promotion of wellness. Wellness is actually a personal choice which incorporates preventive health care into our personal routines. While it sounds relatively simple, many people find it to be too much trouble to stay on schedule with a balanced diet, optimal nutritional supplements, regular exercise and plenty of rest. Yet, those are just the basics.<BR>The basics provide a real foundation. If wellness has never been part of your daily routine, it's not too late to start improving your general health with some minimal lifestyle changes. You'll be genuinely surprised at how good it's possible to feel. Many people accept a much lower quality of life than they deserve, yet, people tend to accept that if they've never experienced anything different.<BR>One perpetual battlefront is weight management. A study completed in December 1995 using Mannatech products MVP caplets and Man&#183;Aloe&#174; capsules in conjunction with an optimal health program that included physical activity and a healthy diet showed that 97% of the subjects in the clinical trial experienced a positive change. The protocol, titled The Metabolic Trim Program, tested two groups of 100 adults. The test was designed to determine the percentage of subjects who could realize a positive change in body composition during a four-week trial period. The change could be loss of fat, gain of lean tissue or both. The overwhelmingly positive results supported results seen in earlier tests. The study was headed by Gilbert R. Kaats, PhD, Director of the Health and Medical Research Foundation in San Antonio, Texas, where the trials took place.<BR>Particular emphasis was placed on the importance of being proactive in developing and supporting the immune system and thus enabling each person the opportunity of functioning at optimal capacity with regard to health and wellness.<BR><BR><B>SUBJECTS</B><BR>Subjects were recruited through newspaper advertising, flyers and by word-of-mouth from people who had either participated in previous Foundation studies or who heard of this study through a Mannatech Associate.<BR>The study's objectives were to examine the effectiveness and the safety of Mannatech's Optimal Health Plan (MOHP) over a period of either four or eight weeks. A total of 528 subjects were recruited. The group was 68% female with an average age of 50.4 years. The remaining 32% was male with an average age of 53.1 years. <BR>Of the 528 subjects, 428 were divided into four separate groups operating in three different locations, each with precise sets of instructions for achieving optimal health. The remaining 100 subjects followed the same plan, but consumed placebos rather than Mannatech phytochemical supplements.Participation in the MOHP involved taking either two or three Mannatech phytochemical supplements daily plus following a lifestyle modification program which included suggestions for increased physical activity, improved nutrition, lifestyle modification techniques and a mild-to-moderate caloric restriction.<BR><BR><B>PROCEDURES, MATERIALS AND METHODS</B><BR>All subjects received a copy of "Living at an Optimal Goal Weight" behavior modification program. This included an activity monitor which measured total daily physical activity, a portable food scale, and the "Living at Goal Weight" manual. Also included were lessons in behavior modification on both audio and video tape.<BR>The subjects, who received either a four- or eight-week supply of Mannatech supplements, recorded daily estimates of their caloric intake, consumption of dietary fat, and daily activity levels as reflected by their activity monitors. Weekly totals were reported during weekly visits to the research center. <BR>Progress was recorded by various methods including comparison of the 50-item Disease/Wellness Symptom Inventory (DWSI) which each subject completed both before beginning the plan and immediately following its completion. Each individual's body composition was measured either by underwater testing (the displacement method) using the Whiter Volumeter or by Lunar Corporation's Dual Energy X-Ray Absorptiometry (DEXA) scanner.<BR>Since product/program efficacy can best be defined as fat loss while maintaining or increasing fat-free mass (FFM), a Body Composition Improvement (BCI) score reflecting positive or negative changes that occurred during the study was calculated for each subject. In calculating the BCI, losses in body fat and increases in FFM were calculated as positive changes. Increases in body fat and decreases in FFM were calculated as negative changes. To illustrate: A subject who lost two lbs. of body fat and gained one lb. of FFM receive a Body Composition Improvement score of +3 while a subject who lost two lbs. of body fat and also lost two pounds of FFM received a BCI score of 0.<BR><BR><B>RESULTS</B><BR>Subjects in all five groups lost significant amounts of body fat without any appreciable loss of lean body mass. When compared to the placebo control group, however, subjects in the four experimental groups (those using phytochemical supplements) lost significantly more body weight and fat. Data from the DWSI revealed that for all self-reported disease symptoms listed, subjects in the phytochemical supplement groups reported improvement. Additionally, subjects in the experimental groups taking Mannatech products reported greater appetite control, less binge eating as measured by an abbreviated Binge Eating Disorder Scale, increased energy levels, improved sleep, and an improvement in general well-being.<BR>A distinctly unique and consistent finding for subjects following the MOHP was that approximately 12% had significant positive changes in their body composition, losing more fat and/or gaining more lean mass than has been observed in any of the other studies the Foundation has conducted on weight loss/health plans. These dramatic changes were found in all four experimental groups using both the underwater and DEXA technology.<BR>Regarding safety and toxicity, five subjects reported mild allergic-like reactions to the product and were discontinued from the study. Using group averages, no adverse effects were observed in any of the 51 blood chemistries measured for any of the five groups. A total of 193 subjects had their blood pressure and resting heart rates measured on a weekly basis, and no significant increases in either of these vital signs were observed.<BR><BR><B>CONCLUSIONS</B><BR>The subjects using the phytochemical supplements in conjunction with the MOHP experienced significant positive changes as evidenced by body composition and self-reported symptoms. The changes observed were significantly greater than those achieved by the subjects who followed the same plan but did not take the phytochemical supplements.<BR><BR><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
