<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Mannatech Tomorrow Online</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><CENTER><A HREF="Tom.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/1aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Fin.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/2aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Ath.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/3aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Pro.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/4aBtn.jpg"></A><A HREF="Act.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/5aBtn.jpg"></A><BR><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/pics/Hma.jpg"></A><BR><BR><A HREF="Tom.html">Tomorrow  |  </A><A HREF="Fin.html">Financial  |  </A><A HREF="Ath.html">Athletics  |  </A><A HREF="Pro.html">Products  |  </A><A HREF="Act.html">Action  |  </A><A HREF="//www.mannatech-inc.com/">Home</A><BR><BR><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><H2>Results</H2><br><I><A HREF="Kaats.html">Back to Optimal Health Plan</A></I><BR><BR></center><H4>An initial analysis of the data for the 8-week phase revealed:</H4><UL><LI>Significant decreases in excess body fat <LI>Maintained or enhanced muscle tissue<LI>Greater appetite control, less "binge" eating, and lowered cravings for high fat foods<LI>Significant decreases in LDL Cholesterol ("harmful" cholesterol)<LI>No adverse effects on blood chemistries or self-reported feelings of well-being<LI>Significant improvements in virtually all of the self-reported symptoms      <UL>               <LI>Headaches               <LI>Chronic tension               <LI>Irritable bowel syndrome               <LI>Lack of energy               <LI>Premenstrual syndrome               <LI>Arthritis               <LI>Recurring sinus infections               <LI>Food allergies               <LI>Tension fatigue syndrome               <LI>Overeating               <LI>Recurrent anxiety               <LI>Stomach pain               <LI>Recurrent depression               <LI>Back pain               <LI>Constipation or diarrhea               <LI>Dizziness               <LI>Inability to concentrate               <LI>Insomnia               <LI>Stomach gas or indigestion               <LI>Self-esteem               <LI>Bad temper or quick to anger               <LI>Binge eating        </UL></UL><p>What is particularly noteworthy about the data is the dramatic changes in body composition for the top ten subjects. In fact, the positive changes in body composition in subjects #1-7 are the most dramatic we have observed after conducting over 20,000 body composition tests in conjunction with previous research studies. Another note of interest is the number and variety of self-reported disease symptoms that were reportedly improved, even from the subjects who did not see noticeable changes in body composition.A word of caution: These results are preliminary and some caution should be exercised in interpreting these data.<p><H4>An analysis of the data from the 4-week program revealed:</H4><UL><LI>97% of the subjects either lost weight or had a positive change in their lean-to-fat ratios.<LI>A total of four people lost 14 or more pounds. The most dramatic weight loss was achieved by a 135 pound woman who lost 14.5 pounds in 30 days, all of which was body fat. Allowing for fluid depletion, she probably gained two pounds of muscle mass.<LI>The most dramatic change in lean-to-fat ratios was achieved by a 171 pound woman who had a 21 pound improvement in her body composition losing 10 pounds of body fat while gaining 11 pounds of lean mass. She was followed closely by a 163 pound woman who had a 17 pound improvement in her body composition, gaining 8 pounds of lean mass and losing 9 pounds of body fat.<p><CENTER><HR WIDTH=100% ALIGN=center SIZE=2><BR><FONT SIZE = 3>Available E-Mail addresses are as follows:<BR><A HREF="mailto:ldaniel@mail.mannatech-inc.com">Customer Service<BR> Email contact for customer service questions and problems.</A><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=-2>Copyright &copy; 1996 Mannatech, Inc. all rights reserved.<BR></FONT></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
