<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Counsel Connect Web - Trade Protection Seminar</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=FFFFFF>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/seminar.gif"></CENTER>

<P><I>Please join us online on Counsel Connect for:</I></P>

<H3>PROTECTING TRADE SECRETS AND CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION:<br>   
HOW SAFE IS YOUR MOST VALUABLE ASSET?</H3>

<P>January 15 - February 4, 1997 in the PRIVATE menu</P>



<P><I>CLE CREDIT AVAILABLE  -- REGISTRATION REQUIRED</I></P>


<P>Your company is a reservoir of confidential information.  Is it adequately protecting its valuable business secrets?  Preventing intrusions into paper and computer files?  Averting the use or disclosure of proprietary information when an employee moves to a competitor?    On the flip side, how is your company avoiding the risk of using someone else’s trade secrets when new employees come aboard?</P>



<P>Join this seminar to get the information and tools you need to safeguard your company's files and maintain their confidentiality. You’ll learn how to: </P>

<UL>
<LI>Define a trade secret and determine whether one exists 

<LI>Draft non-compete and confidentiality agreements that prevent employees from walking away with and using your crucial information 

<LI>Maintain information security

<LI>Understand the limits on restricting access to and use of confidential information 
<LI>Litigate a trade secrets case
<LI>Frame protective orders and injunctions  
</UL>

<P>Moderated by <B>VICTORIA  A. CUNDIFF</B> of Paul, Hastings, Janofsky & Walker, NY, this program features an outstanding group of panelists including: </P>
<BR CLEAR>

<P><B>WILLIAM COATS</B>, Howry & Simon, Menlo Park, CA </P>

<P><B>PROF. MICHAEL J. HUTTER</B>, Albany Law School, Albany, NY</P>

<P><B>BRADFORD P. LYERLA</B>, Jenner & Block, Chicago, IL  </P>

<P><B>M. MARGARET McKEOWN</B>, Perkins Coie, Seattle, WA  </P>

<P><B>ROBERT A. MERRING</B>, Attorney at Law, Newport Beach, CA </P>

<P><B>DEIRDRE K. MULLIGAN</B>, Center for Democracy and Technology, Washington, DC </P>

<P><B>JANET T. MUNN</B>, Steel Hector & Davis, Miami, FL </P>

<P><B>HEATHER D. RAFTER</B>, Digidesign, Inc., Menlo Park, CA </P>

<P><B>LAURENCE H. REECE III</B>, Heidlage & Reece, Boston, MA </P>

<P>Attend for just $79. To register for the seminar complete the <A HREF="enroll.html">Registration Form</A> and fax it back 212-692-7855, ATTN:  <A HREF="mailto:laurie.gordon@counsel.com">Laurie Gordon</A>, Executive Editor, Counsel Connect.  You must be a Counsel Connect member to attend this program.  To join Counsel Connect complete the Join Counsel Connect <A HREF="/inside/join.html">membership application</A> or call 800-569-4086.</P>

<CENTER><P><TT><FONT SIZE="-1">Counsel Connect certifies that this activity has been approved for<BR>MCLE credit by the State Bar of California in the amount of 3 hours.</FONT></TT></P></CENTER>

