<BR CLEAR=ALL>


<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG WIDTH=232 HEIGHT=30 BORDER=0  SRC="http://www.counsel.com/images/epicks.gif" ALIGN=CENTER ALT="Editor's Picks"></P>





<BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><B>Week of January 6th:</B></FONT></P>







<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.cpsc.gov">Consumer Products Safety Commission</A></FONT></br>

Who investigated reports of dangerous Cabbage Patch
Snacktime Dolls?  Get comfortable with the independent
federal agency that protects the public from the
unreasonable risk of injury or death from 15,000
types of consumer products. The Commission
posts news, recall notices and publications about
safety.




<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://eva.dc.lsoft.com/archives/net-lawyers.html">Net-Lawyers Archives</A></FONT><BR>

Netiquette for lawyers.  Online marketing.  Law firm
home pages.  Intranets,  Web resources. Listen in as
top Internet-savvy lawyers discuss the online
world and the practice of law.  Searchable archives of
Lew Rose's Net-lawyers listserv goes back to November
1996, and grows weekly.






<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.lawcircle.com/observer/">Computer Law Observer</A></FONT><BR>

From Maryland attorney William S. Galkin comes a free
monthly e-letter covering "a wide range of cutting-edge
legal issues relating to computers, technology and the
Internet."  Read back issues and subscribe onsite
to receive the Observer via e-mail.


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.olsen.ch/cgi-bin/exmenu">Currency Converter</A></FONT><BR>

Pesos, pounds, lira. Rupees, yen, kuna.
Find out how much your dollars are worth across the
globe. Use this simple databank to find the exchange
rate for any day since January 1, 1980 for 164
currencies.  From Olsen & Associates, Ltd., a
Zurich-based developer of online forecasting
technology for business and finance.


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.ctg.albany.edu/projects/inettb/recintro.html">Developing & Delivering Government Services
on the World Wide Web</A></FONT><BR>

Lawyers appreciate well-made government Web sites
and here's the handbook that tells the government how
to build them.  The Center for Technology in Government
at the State University of New York at Albany
presents a detailed guide for government agencies
ready to create and deliver Web sites.






<P><B>Also check our <A HREF="picksarchive.html">Editor's Picks Archive</A>.</B></P>



</BLOCKQUOTE>

</BLOCKQUOTE>



