<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/counselquote/cquoteheader2.gif" ALT="Counsel Quote by Counsel Connect"></A>
</TD>
</TR>
 
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT>
<A HREF="/counselquote/hottop.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/counselquote/cqhottops.gif" ALT="Hot Topics"></A><BR CLEAR=ALL>
&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT SIZE="3"><TT>Aloha to Gay Marriage?</TT></FONT>
<A HREF="/images/cquotedirectory.map"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/counselquote/cquotedirectory.gif" WIDTH=225 HEIGHT=285 ALT="Directory" ISMAP></A>
</TD>

<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<P><A HREF="hottop.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/counselquote/cqsmwelcome2.gif" ALT="WELCOME"></A><BR CLEAR=ALL>
<FONT SIZE=-1>
Everyday, the members of Counsel Connect discuss the news from a unique perspective, be it a blockbuster Supreme Court decision or new legislation. Counsel Connect is open only to practicing lawyers, however. So when a hot issue is burning up a discussion forum, we post excerpts of it on Counsel Quote's <A HREF="/counselquote/hottop.html">Hot Topics</A> page.</P>

<P>You might have more particular needs, though. Need a source for a story? Go to the <A HREF="/counselquote/media.html">Queries</A> area to tell us your question -- we'll post it on Counsel Connect for our members to see. Or check our listing of experts by specialty -- like antitrust, criminal law and many others -- by using the <A HREF="/counselquote/experts.html">Experts On Call</A> area. Want to poll lawyers about a particular issue? We'll do it for you with <A HREF="/counselquote/canvas.html">Counsel Canvass</A>. Need an idea for a legal story? Check <A HREF="/counselquote/stories.html">Story Ideas</A>, where attorneys present you with topics they think may be exciting. You can also search a database of Counsel Connect members and other lawyers by going to <A HREF="/lawyersearch/">Lawyer Search</A>.</P>

<P>So add Counsel Quote to your bookmark file. And when there's an issue for which you need an articulate, well-educated legal viewpoint, don't reach for your phone, reach for your mouse and call up Counsel Quote.</P></FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
