        <TR>
        <TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=2>
                <TABLE WIDTH=320 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1>
                <TR>
                <TD>
                <FONT SIZE=+0>
				<p><a href="/features/keat.html"><b>Charles Keating: Scoundrel or Scapegoat? </b></a></FONT>
						
				<BR><FONT SIZE=-1>
 The man who symbolized the savings-and-loan crisis of the late 1980s is free -- a federal judge has 
 overturned Charles Keating Jr's 1993 racketeering, conspiracy and fraud convictions.  But is Keating innocent?
 Listen in as a panel of experts, including Keating's lawyer and prosecutor, discuss the Keating
 affair. 

A Web exclusive from the <a href="/inside/join.html">Counsel Connect</A> Criminal Law forum.

	



				
				
				
				<p>
				</FONT>
                </TD>
                </TR> </TABLE>
        </TD>
        </TR>

        <TR>
        <TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=2>
               <TABLE ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=330 BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>
                <TR>
                <TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=CENTER BGCOLOR=FFFFFF>
