<title>Counsel Connect Web: Free Ride For Rapists?</title>
<BODY bgcolor=ffffff text="000000" link="000080" vlink="ff0000">


<img align=left src="http://www.counsel.com/images/lcc.gif"> 
 <blockquote>
<font color=ff0000 size=+2>Perjury Plea for Former Detective</font>
<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>


October 7, 1996<P>
<BLOCKQUUOTE><PRE>
<B><B>CRIMINAL LAW & PROCEDURE<P>

[Editor's Note:</B> Mark Fuhrman will serve three years on 
probation in his new home state of Idaho. Prosecutors and Fuhrman, 
a former LAPD Detective, reached this sentencing agreement 
regarding perjury charges. Fuhrman pled nolo contendre to the 
charges stemming from his testimony in the trial of O.J. Simpson 
for the murders of Nicole Brown Simpson and Ron Goldman.]

<B>DANIEL E. LUNGREN
Attorney General
GEORGE WILLIAMSON
Chief Assistant Attorney General
CAROL WENDELIN POLLACK
Senior Assistant Attorney General
JOHN GORDNIER, State Bar No. 45250
Senior Assistant Attorney General
EUGENE KASTER, State Bar No. 42900
Deputy Attorney General
DAVID F. GLASSMAN, State Bar No. ll5664
Deputy Attorney General
Office of the Attorney General
300 South Spring St.
Los Angeles, CA 90013
Telephone: (213) 897-2355
Attorneys for Plaintiffs

       SUPERIOR COURT OF THE STATE OF
                 CALIFORNIA
            COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES
              CENTRAL DISTRICT
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA,
Plaintiff,
v.
MARK FUHRMAN,
Defendant.</B>


Original Charge: Count I: Violation of Penal Code section 118
                 (a felony)
