<H2><a href=vol6.htm><B>VOLUME VI</B></a></H2>


<H3>COMMENTS ON
FDA's PROPOSED REGULATIONS:<BR>
PART 897<BR>
GENERAL COMMENTS AND COMMENTS ON<BR>
SUBPARTS
A-C</H3>

PART 897<P>
GENERAL COMMENTS..............  VI-1<P>
I.  PART
897 IS PRECLUDED BY SECTION 1926 OF THE<BR>
PUBLIC HEALTH SERVICE ACT, ENACTED BY
THE<BR>
ADAMHA REORGANIZATION ACT OF 1992........ VI-5<P>
A.  Part 897 Impermissibly
Abridges<BR>
 Power That Congress Has Expressly<BR>
Recognized Belongs to the States......
VI-10<P>
B.  Since the FDCA Broadly Preempts<BR>
 State Law on Medical Devices,<BR>

Section 1926 of the PHS Act Makes<BR>
 Clear That Congress Does Not Intend<BR>
 That FDA
Regulate Tobacco Products<BR>
as Medical Devices............ VI-14<P>
 C.  Even If
Tobacco Products Could Be<BR>
Regulated as Medical Devices,<BR>
Congress Has Reserved to
the States<BR>
the Power To Decide How Youth Access<BR>
to Such Alleged "Medical
Devices"<BR>
Should Be Regulated..........  VI-15<P>
II.  PART 897 IS PRECLUDED BY THE
FEDERAL<BR>
CIGARETTE LABELING AND ADVERTISING ACT........ VI-17<P>
A.  FCLAA
Expressly Precludes FDA's<BR>
 Proposed Cigarette Advertising,<BR>
Promotion, and Labeling
Regulations......   VI-18<P>
B.  FDA's Proposed Regulations Are<BR>
Impliedly
Precluded by the FCLAA...... VI-31<P>
1. The Proposed FDA Regulations<BR>
