<H2><B>VOLUME  
VIII</B></H2>

<H3>Sorry, Volume 8 is not yet available</H3>


<H3>EXPERT COMMENTS ON ADVERTISING AND RELATED ISSUES</H3>

Introductory Statement<P>
1.   Professor Timothy P.
Meyer<P>
Marketing, Advertising, Mass Media and Consumer Behavior,<BR>
Ben J. and
Joyce Rosenberg Professor, University of<BR>
Wisconsin<BR>
(CV attached)<P>
A Ban On
Color And Imagery In Cigarette Advertising<BR>
Is Tantamount To A Ban On Cigarette
Advertising<P>
FDA's Proposal To Ban Imagery and Color In Outdoor<BR>
Advertising For
Cigarettes Is Unsupported By The<BR>
Record And Is Tantamount To A Ban On
Outdoor<BR>
Advertising<P>
FDA Cites No Evidence Of Any Causal Connection<BR>
Between
Exposure To Cigarette Advertising And The<BR>
Decision To Smoke<P>
2.  Professor
Edward V. Morse<P>
Clinical Professor of Psychiatry, Louisiana State<BR>
