<HEAD>

<TITLE>Networking</TITLE>
        <META>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" VLINK="000000" LINK="000000"><A NAME="TOP"><TABLE><TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER WITDTH="20%"><IMG SRC="images/LOGO.GIF"></TD>
                
                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="60%">
                        <IMG SRC="images/JOINHEAD.GIF">
                </TD>

                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="20%">
                        <A HREF="join.html"><IMG SRC="images/JOINLOOP.GIF" BORDER=0></A>
                </TD>
        </TR>
</TABLE><P>

<font color="ff1111" font size=5><center>Connecting Lawyers to Lawyers
</CENTER></FONT><P>


Looking for a quick lead on a case cite?  Want to see if anyone knows where to find an expert witness in a particular area?  Interested in debating a new decision in your practice area?  Visit one of Counsel Connect's discussion groups and you'll find colleagues ready to help out -- or join in the discussion.<P>

Each of our 200 discussion groups covers a different topic, and most are moderated by well known-experts in that area.  Whether you're interested in securities law, medical malpractice or law practice management, there's a discussion group where you can connect with other lawyers to get the information you need.  And Counsel Connect's legal editors post copies of new cases and other useful information in those discussion groups so that participants have quick access to relevant materials.  Discussion groups are easy on your schedule: post a comment in the morning (or anytime you want) and come back when it's convenient to read the responses.

</P>
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
        <TR>
                <TD ALIGN=RIGHT>
