<HEAD>

<TITLE>Managing Your Practice</TITLE>
        <META>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" VLINK="000000" LINK="000000">

<TABLE><TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER WITDTH="20%"><IMG SRC="images/LOGO.GIF"></TD>
                
                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="60%">
                        <IMG SRC="images/JOINHEAD.GIF">
                </TD>

                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="20%">
                        <A HREF="join.html"><IMG SRC="images/JOINLOOP.GIF" BORDER=0></A>
                </TD>
        </TR>
</TABLE><P>


<FONT color="000000" font size=5><CENTER>A Host Of Resources To Help You Manage Your Practice.</CENTER></B> </font><BR>

<p>

<font color="ff1111" font size=3>Discussion Groups.</font>  Whether you need a quick case cite, the name of a relevant legal treatise, feedback on time and billing software packages or the name of a good expert witness, you will find Counsel Connect members who can help.  Rather than spending your scarce time tracking down the information you need, just take a minute and post a quick note in one of our 200 discussion groups.  Then check back later that day (or that week) to see who has responded.<p>

<font color="ff1111" font size=3>Legal Products and Services.</font>  Every day you are faced with an increasing number of choices about which products and services to use for your law practice.  Counsel Connect's Resources menu contains information about a wide variety of legal products and services that will help you to make informed choices.  Better yet, the companies selling these products and services are available by e-mail, allowing you to contact them with your questions easily.<p>

<font color="ff1111" font size=3>Communication.</font>  Counsel Connect's e-mail and private conferencing features can help you cut down -- or even eliminate -- fax and overnight charges.  Instead of sending out a document by fax or courier, you can send that same document by e-mail -- saving you time and money.  If you are working with a group of attorneys, you can make documents available to co-counsel by setting up a secure private room -- thereby cutting down on the inevitable calls asking for copies of different documents.<p>

<font color="ff1111" font size=3>Internet.</font>  There is a huge amount of valuable legal information on the Internet -- information that other companies normally charge a lot of money to provide.  Counsel Connect's Internet connection allows you to get those materials at a fraction of what they ordinarily cost.  And our free Lawlinks service puts those materials at your fingertips.<p>

Of course, these are just a few examples of how Counsel Connect can help you manage your practice more effectively -- your Counsel Connect membership includes free training, and our customer service staff will be happy to explore all of the ways that Counsel Connect can benefit your practice.<P>

