<HEAD>

<TITLE>New Business</TITLE>
	<META>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" VLINK="000000" LINK="000000"><A NAME="TOP"><TABLE><TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER WITDTH="20%"><IMG SRC="images/LOGO.GIF"></TD>
                
                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="60%">
                        <IMG SRC="images/JOINHEAD.GIF">
                </TD>

                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="20%">
                        <A HREF="join.html"><IMG SRC="images/JOINLOOP.GIF" BORDER=0></A>
                </TD>
        </TR>
</TABLE><P>

<font color="000000" font size=5><center>Build Your Practice -- Online.<BR> </CENTER></FONT><P>

When you join Counsel Connect, a whole world of opportunities to meet new clients and develop new business relationships will open up for you.  Here's how:<P>

<B><font color="ff1111" font size=3>Discussion Groups</FONT></B><BR>

Participating in Counsel Connect's discussion groups is one of the most effective ways to develop professional relationships that lead to new opportunities.  When you join in online dicussions -- whether to debate a recent decision or help out another member with a tip or a case cite -- you'll get to know colleagues just as you do in person.  And when your online colleagues need to retain a lawyer with your experience, you'll be the person they contact.<P>

<B><font color="ff1111" font size=3> Lawyer Inquiries</FONT></B><BR>

Every day Counsel Connect members post notices in our Inquiries areas looking for counsel with particular expertise.  Whether they need advice on California tax law or a lawyer with medical malpractice experience in Boston, our members have discovered that Counsel Connect is the fastest way to find lawyers with the right experience.  And if you're that lawyer, checking out Counsel Connect's Inquiries areas regularly will pay off for your practice.<P>


<B><font color="ff1111" font size=3>Online Publishing </FONT></B><BR>

As a Counsel Connect member, you can get the word out about your area of expertise by publishing your articles or other written documents online.  Just e-mail us the material and we'll load them in our searchable online library, where other members interested in those topics can find it -- and you.<P>


<B><font color="ff1111" font size=3>New Business Panels</FONT></B><BR>

Counsel Connect 's "Quick Request for Proposals" service allows in-house counsel and non-lawyer business people to e-mail descriptions of matters for which they need to hire counsel to panels of Counsel Connect members experienced in that area.  Interested panel members can contact the sender with their qualifications and a description of how they would handle the matter and on what terms.<P>
<TABLE WIDTH="100%">
        <TR>
                <TD ALIGN=LEFT>
                        <B><font color="ff1111" font size=3><A HREF="inside.html"><IMG SRC="images/RETURN.GIF" BORDER=0></A></B> </font>
                </TD>
                <TD ALIGN=CENTER>
                        <A HREF="join.html"><IMG SRC="images/JOIN2.GIF" BORDER=0></A>
                </TD>
        </TR>
</TABLE>
