<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>Communications</TITLE>
        <META>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" VLINK="000000" LINK="000000"><A NAME="TOP"><TABLE><TABLE WIDTH="100%" BORDER=0><TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER WITDTH="20%"><IMG SRC="images/LOGO.GIF"></TD>
                
                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="60%">
                        <IMG SRC="images/JOINHEAD.GIF">
                </TD>

                <TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH="20%">
                        <A HREF="join.html"><IMG SRC="images/JOINLOOP.GIF" BORDER=0></A>
                </TD>
        </TR>
</TABLE><P>

<font color="ff1111" font size=5><center>Communications</CENTER></FONT></P>

<B><font color="000000" font size=3></FONT></B><BR>

Counsel Connect's communication features -- our unique private conferencing service and comprehensive e-mail system -- will help make your law practice more efficient and allow you to spend less time on administrative activities (not to mention less money on overnight and fax charges):<p>

<B><font color="ff1111" font size=3>PRIVATE CONFERENCING</FONT></B><BR>

Counsel Connect's "Private" feature allows you to create your own online "conference rooms" where you can store documents, share information and hold discussions with other lawyers.  It takes only a minute or two to setup a private room and, once created, a private room remains online as long as you want.  Private rooms are secure, and no one but you and the Counsel Connect members you select have access to the private rooms you create.</P>

<P>
Private rooms can help save you time and money in a variety of situations.  Here are just two examples:</P>

<BLOCKQUOTE><font color="ff1111" font size=3>Ongoing matters:</FONT>  You and co-counsel can set up a private room to store and exchange materials (such as depositions, drafts, etc.).  Instead of faxing documents (or sending them by overnight mail) to everyone, you can store them in the private room, thereby making them available to co-counsel instantly -- and at a fraction of the cost.</BR><BR>
<font color="ff1111" font size=3>Bar association work:</FONT>  You and other members of the bar committees you serve on can create private rooms where you can hold online discussions and work on bar matters.</BLOCKQUOTE></BR>

<P>There is no charge for creating private rooms, and you may create as many as you wish.</P>


<P>
<B><font color="ff1111" font size=3>E-MAIL</FONT></B><BR>

Counsel Connect's e-mail system is easy to use and allows you to connect with virtually anyone on the information highway.  Our document attachment feature allows you to send documents (a draft of a brief, a contract or anything stored on your computer) by e-mail with a click of your mouse.  That means no more waiting for overnight mail or sending expensive faxes.  Also, Counsel Connect uses state of the art security, so you can rest assured that your communications are secure.<P>


