<HtMl>

<head>

<title> 

Counsel Connect Online Seminars

</title>

</head>

<body bgcolor=ffffff vlink=ff0000>

<P align=center>

<a href="http://www.counsel.com/cgi-bin/htimage/images/archive.map">

<img ISMAP width=458 height=53 border=0 src="/images/seminar.gif"

alt="COUNSEL CONNECT SEMINARS"></a>

</P>





Please join us online on Counsel Connect for:



<FONT COLOR="42426F"> <H2>PROTECTING TRADE SECRETS AND CONFIDENTIAL

INFORMATION:<BR>

HOW SAFE IS YOUR MOST VALUABLE ASSET?</H2></FONT>



<H3>January 15 - February 4, 1997</H3>



<P>CLE CREDIT AVAILABLE  -- REGISTRATION REQUIRED</P>





<P>Your company is a reservoir of confidential information.  Is it

adequately protecting its valuable business secrets?  Preventing

intrusions into paper and computer files?  Averting the use or

disclosure of proprietary information when an employee moves to a

competitor?    On the flip side, how is your company avoiding the

risk of using someone else’s trade secrets when new employees come

aboard?  </P>

<P>

Join this seminar to get the information and tools you need to

safeguard your company's files and maintain their confidentiality.

From a panel of experts drawn from law firms, corporations, law

schools and the government, you’ll learn how to:

<UL>

<LI> Define a trade secret and determine whether one exists

 

<LI> Draft non-compete and confidentiality agreements that prevent

employees from walking away with and using your crucial information

 

<LI>Understand the in-house view of trade secrets



<LI> Maintain information security

 

<LI> Understand the limits on restricting access to and use of

confidential information

 

<LI> Litigate a trade secrets case: the key strategies and tactics

 

<LI> Frame protective orders and injunctions



<LI>Deal with the recently-enacted Economic Espionage Act, which

makes the theft of trade secrets a federal crime

</UL>

<P>

Moderated by VICTORIA  A. CUNDIFF of Paul, Hastings, Janofsky &

Walker, NY, this program features an outstanding group of panelists

including:

<P>



WILLIAM SLOAN COATS, <SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10><I>Howrey &

Simon, Menlo Park, CA</I>

<BR>

PROF. MICHAEL J. HUTTER,<SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10> <I>Albany

Law School, Albany, NY</I> 

<BR>

BRADFORD P. LYERLA, <SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10><I>Jenner &

Block, Chicago, IL </I>

<BR>

M. MARGARET McKEOWN,<SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10> <I>Perkins Coie,

Seattle, WA</I> 

<BR>

ROBERT A. MERRING,<SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10> <I>Attorney at

Law, Newport Beach, CA</I>

<BR>

DEIRDRE K. MULLIGAN,<SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10> <I>Center for

Democracy and Technology,

Washington, DC</I>

<BR>

JANET T. MUNN, <SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10><I>Steel Hector &

Davis, Miami, FL</I>

<BR>

HEATHER D. RAFTER,<SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10> <I>Digidesign,

Inc., Menlo Park, CA</I>

<BR>

LAURENCE H. REECE III,<SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10><I>Heidlage &

Reece, Boston, MA</I>

<BR>

PETER TOREN, <SPACER TYPE=HORIZONTAL SIZE=10><I>Computer Crimes

Division, U.S. Department of Justice,

Washington, DC</I>

<P>

You get all this -- useful, important information, and the wisdom and

experience of our panelists -- for just $79. To register for the

seminar, just complete the form below and fax it to Laurie C. Gordon,

Executive Editor, Counsel Connect at 212 692 7855.  

<P>

<BR CLEAR>



<P>

*******************************************************************



