<img width=325 height=30 border=0  src="/images/eparchive.gif" alt="EDITOR'S 
PICK'S ARCHIVE">

</P>






<BLOCKQUOTE>

<B><FONT color="000000">Here's a collection of our editor's picks from weeks
gone by. Counsel Connect law 

editors continually monitor the Net, tracking interesting legal and government
sites so you don't have

to.</FONT></B></BLOCKQUOTE>

</P>


<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of December 30th:</B></TT></B></font>
</P>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://free.websight.com/10/">NABANet: The Native American Bar Association Network</A></FONT></br>

<UL>Meet the Native American Bar Association, founded in 
1971 by American Indian, Alaska Native, and Native 
Hawaiian attorneys and attorneys who practice federal 
Indian law. Boasting nearly 2000 members from federally- 
recognized Indian tribes and other native groups in 
the United States, NABA offers links and other resources.

</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.sbaonline.sba.gov/business_finances/
FinancingYourBusiness.html">SBA: Financing Your Business</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>Start a business in 1997.  Visit the Small Business 
Administration for a deep pocket of resources covering 
"loans and venture capital financing" for "small businesses
unable to secure financing through normal
lending channels."  Find out about programs 
including FA$TRAK, CAPLines, minority and 
women's loans, and more. 

</P>
</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.legalonline.com/courts.htm">State Laws on the Internet</A></FONT><BR>

<UL>Looking for state laws from Alabama to Wyoming?  
Grab this handy guide for links to state bills and 
statutes on the Web.  From legal.online editor 
Bob Ambrogi

</P>
</UL>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://ttnwww.rtpnc.epa.gov/naaqspro/press.htm">EPA's Proposed New Air Quality Standards</A></FONT><BR>

<UL>Heads up:  The EPA is seeking to revise the ozone 
and particulate matter national ambient air quality 
standards (NAAQS) and the proposed particulate matter 
monitoring requirements.  Read the new proposals and
plan to attend a public hearing to spew forth what
you think about all this hot air.
</P>
</UL>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://ciac.llnl.gov/ciac/CIACHoaxes.html">Internet Hoaxes</A></FONT><BR>

<UL>Virus or hoax?  Some naughty netizens enjoy a practical 
joke.  Here to get serious about computer viruses
is the Department of Energy's Computer Incident
Advisory Capability (CIAC).  Get to the bottom of recent
hoaxes such as Good Timnes, Ghost, PENPAL,
Irina, and Make Money Fast.  Be careful out there.


</P>
</UL>
</ul>



<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of December 23rd:</B></TT></B></font>
</P>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.legalonline.com/courts.htm">Where To Find Court Opinions</A></FONT></br>

<UL>Where do netizens find opinions of the Supreme Court

and all federal circuit courts? Where are home pages for

district courts and bankruptcy courts? How about

state courts decisions from Alabama to Wyoming?

Use this handy and newly updated guide for links to court

opinions on the Web, along with pointers to legal opinion

databases in cybertown. From legal.online editor

Bob Ambrogi.
</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.netlaw.com">NetLaw</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>From Lance Rose, the author of NetLaw - Your Rights

in the Online World, and U.K. barrister Nick Lockett,

here's a new "transatlantic" Web house. Featuring

cyberspace law resources, and an overview on how to

"Build a Safer Web Site." With links to and

summaries of important cases. NetLaw also offers

Web site legal audits, designed to spot and

remedy your online risks.

</P>
</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.dreamscape.com/frankvad/search.legal.html">Virtual Legal Search Engines</A></FONT><BR>

<UL>FindLaw to LawCrawler, Hieros Gamos to LawInfo.

Meta-Index for Legal Research. Here's a collection

of links to legal search engines, directories,

and other snappy web-smart tools for e-lawyers.

Dig in.
</P>
</UL>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.whitehouse.gov/fsbr/esbr.html">Economic Statistics Briefing Room (ESBR)</A></FONT><BR>

<UL>Per capita income. The consumer price index.

Crude oil prices, interest rates and bond yields.

If numbers are your thing, ring up this wealth

of economic indicators, produced and updated by

a variety of number-crunching federal agencies.

</P>
</UL>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.abanet.org/ceeli">Central and East European Law Initiative (CEELI)</A></FONT><BR>

<UL>Get to know CEELI, the ABA's "project to advance the

rule of law in the world by supporting the law reform

process underway in Central and Eastern Europe and

the New Independent States of the former Soviet Union."

With volunteer opportunities, discussions, overview

of CEELI programs and a collection of links.

</P>
</UL>
</ul>











<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of December
16th:</B></TT></B></font>
</P>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.wsj.com">Wall Street Journal Interactive
Edition</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>Subscribe to the Interactive Edition for all the
top news and marketplace information enhanced with
Web features, including Personal Journal (to customize
your news and track stocks and funds) and smartly
linked "company snapshots" and "briefing books."
Winner of the 1996 National Information Infrastructure
Award for business.
</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.iahc.org">Internet
International Ad Hoc Committee</A></FONT><BR><UL>
Meet the IAHC -- netizens from the Internet Society,
trademark organizations and other groups gathered
to work on policies for managing and revising the
Internet Domain Name System. Read papers by committee
members, along with drafts, standards and other documents.
Submit your own proposals. And travel to related domain
name, trademark and cyberlaw sites.</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://stic.neu.edu/">State Tobacco Information
Center</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Attorneys general across the country are suing the
tobacco industry to recover medical costs associated with
treating tobacco-related disease. Former Maine
Attorney General Jim Tierney presents a library
of key litigation documents in these pending
actions, compiled from AG offices, outside
counsel, Court TV and Counsel Connect libraries.</P>
</UL>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/icc/
">International Criminal Court Home Page
</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Does the world need an international criminal court
(ICC)? The NGO Coalition for an International
Criminal Court, along with other justice-minded
groups, thinks so. Read about the "proposed permanent
international tribunal empowered to try individuals
for gross violations of international law."</P>
</UL>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A
HREF="http://www.hq.nasa.gov/office/pao/NewsRoom/today.html">Today@NASA
</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Life on Mars? Ice on the moon? Get the latest far-
out news from the National Aeronautics and Space
Administration. With shuttle mission schedules, photos,
a space calendar, news archives and more. Lift-off.</P>
</UL>
</UL>

</P>


<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of December 9th:</B></TT></B></font>
</P>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.netreach.net/~wmanning/">The Health Law Resource</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Telemedicine. Bioethics. Medical records privacy. Medicare. Medicaid. Healthcare industry mergers. Examine a site for health care lawyers and professionals that focuses on "regulatory and transactional aspects of health care law practice." With articles, "issues of the month," and pointers to related sites. From William L. Manning of Dechert Price & Rhoads.</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.city.net/">City.Net</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Visiting clients across the globe? Planning a cosmopolitan vacation? From New York to Atlanta to L.A., Vancouver to Vienna, hit the streets at Excite's City.Net. Visit the concierge and scour e-maps. And travel to the most popular U.S. and international cities on the Web. Bon voyage.</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.arraydev.com:80/commerce/JIBC/">Journal of Internet Banking and Commerce</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Get a Canadian perspective on the brave e-world of digital commerce with a bimonthly journal from north of the border. Read articles covering the range of issues in online commerce, including encryption, the role of banks in Internet biz, telecommunications, trade, and security issues. Browse an archive of past issues.</P>
</UL>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.law.vill.edu:80/tax/index.html">Villanova Tax Law Compendium</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
The Villanova Center for Information Law and Policy presents a long-scrolling catalog of student and faculty tax law papers. Catch up on tax treatment of asbestos removal costs to state income taxation of non-resident professional athletes.</P>
</UL>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.commlaw.com/pepper/Memos/memos.html">Communications Law Memos</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
What's happening in the wired world of communications? Tune in to Pepper & Corazzini's home page for a collection of memos covering international and domestic telecommunications law developments from digital TV standards and satellite licensing rules, to cable regulatory fees and FCC rules on indecent programming.</P>
</UL>
</UL>

<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of December 2nd:</B></TT></B></font>
</P>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.netreach.net/~wmanning/">The Health Law Resource</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Telemedicine. Bioethics. Medical records privacy. Medicare. Medicaid. Healthcare industry mergers. Examine a site for health care lawyers and professionals that focuses on "regulatory and transactional aspects of health care law practice." With articles, "issues of the month," and pointers to related sites. From William L. Manning of Dechert Price & Rhoads.</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.city.net/">City.Net</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Visiting clients across the globe? Planning a cosmopolitan vacation? From New York to Atlanta to L.A., Vancouver to Vienna, hit the streets at Excite's City.Net. Visit the concierge and scour e-maps. And travel to the most popular U.S. and international cities on the Web. Bon voyage.</P>
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.arraydev.com:80/commerce/JIBC/">Journal of Internet Banking and Commerce</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
Get a Canadian perspective on the brave e-world of digital commerce with a bimonthly journal from north of the border. Read articles covering the range of issues in online commerce, including encryption, the role of banks in Internet biz, telecommunications, trade, and security issues. Browse an archive of past issues.</P>
</UL>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.law.vill.edu:80/tax/index.html">Villanova Tax Law Compendium</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
The Villanova Center for Information Law and Policy presents a long-scrolling catalog of student and faculty tax law papers. Catch up on tax treatment of asbestos removal costs to state income taxation of non-resident professional athletes.</P>
</UL>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF="http://www.commlaw.com/pepper/Memos/memos.html">Communications Law Memos</A></FONT><BR>
<UL>
What's happening in the wired world of communications? Tune in to Pepper & Corazzini's home page for a collection of memos covering international and domestic telecommunications law developments from digital TV standards and satellite licensing rules, to cable regulatory fees and FCC rules on indecent programming.</P>
</UL>
</UL>



<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of November 25th:</B></TT></B></font>
</P>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://edms.esrin.esa.it/ecsl/index.html>European Centre for Space Law</A></FONT>
<BR>
<UL>
Founded in 1989, with membership open to European individuals and institutions, ECSL is on a mission is to facilitate space law research, education and practice in Europe.  Rocket over to this site for ECSL bulletins, information about upcoming conferences. And apply to the ECSL secretariat for access ESALEX, a Web-based database of international space law texts, articles and treaties.
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://patents.cnidr.org/patbib_index.html>U.S. Patents at CNIDR</a></b>
<br><UL>
Courtesy of the Center for Networked Information Discovery and Retrieval, search a database of U.S. patents bibliographic data from 1976. Browse the U.S. patents classifications database. And follow the pointer to the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.
</UL>
</A></FONT>

<BR>


<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.qrd.org/qrd/www/usa/legal/lgln/>Lesbian/Gay Law Notes</A></FONT>

<BR><UL>
From Queer Resources Directory, dip into an archive of Lesbian/Gay Law Notes, a publication of the Lesbian and Gay Law Association of Greater New York. Edited by professor Arthur Leonard of New York Law School, the monthly newsletter covers issues in gay jurisprudence.
</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://njlawnet.com/njlaw_t.html>New Jersey Law Network</A></FONT>

<BR><UL>
Take a spin around the Garden State via the site devoted to New Jersey legal resources including courts, legal organizations, government agencies, state statutes, pending legislation and legal news. With lots of nonlegal New Jersey resources along with general law pointers.
</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.techstocks.com>Silicon Investor</A></FONT>

<BR><UL>
Is the Web paved with e-gold?  Dip into the award-winning financial resource for netizens interested in technology stocks. Focusing on publicly-traded tech companies in the U.S., Silicon Investor features quotes, charts, discussion forums and links.
</UL>
</UL>
<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of November 18th:</B></TT></B></font>

</P>









<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.parliament.the-stationery-office.co.uk/pa/home.htm>United Kingdom Parliament</A></FONT>

<BR>

<UL>

We have Congress. They have Parliament. Parliament came first. Stroll over to the United Kingdom for information on the U.K's legislative body, its members, committees and publications. Visit the House of Lords and the House of Commons. Read transcripts of parliamentary debates, updated daily. Tally ho.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.featherslaw.com/tech/tech.htm>Software and Technology Law Resources</a></b>

<br><UL>

From Kansas City attorney Timothy J. Feathers of Hillix, Brewer, Hoffhaus, Whittaker & Wright, here's a collection of pointers to recent cases, newsletters, articles, journals, resources and sites covering technology and cyberspace law, patents, copyright, trademarks and more. Register to receive an e-mail notice whenever new links arrive.

</UL>

</A></FONT>



<BR>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.bnet.att.com/businessbookmarks/>Business Bookmarks</A></FONT>



<BR><UL>

Sales and marketing. Industries and companies. News and resources. AT&T Business Network offers up a databank of hand-picked, annotated and neatly organized destinations for business-minded netizens. The Web means e-biz.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://ilw.com>Immigration Lawyers on the Web</A></FONT>



<BR><UL> 

Here's a Web spot where potential clients all over the world can find immigration lawyers. Featuring a database of immigration counsel and the American Immigration Lawyers Association's searchable membership index. With links to immigration newsgroups, translation services, legal resources and human rights organizations.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.legalethics.com/states.htm>State Bars and Ethics Updates</A></FONT>



<BR><UL>

How are state bars regulating the profession's use of the information superhighway? Legalethics.com tracks bar action in all states, the District of Columbia, and reports on the work of the ABA on ethical law practice in cyberspace. Select a state for bar contact information. And check back for updates. 

</UL>

</ul>


<UL>
<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of November 11th:</B></TT></B></font>

</P>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.mcs.net/~pmccaul/energy>EnergyLinks</A></FONT>

<BR>

<UL>

Looking for energy on the Web?  Plug into EnergyLinks for energy cooperatives, municipal utilities, federally-owned power providers, public utilities, and other energy companies. Learn about energy career and investment opportunities and review the SEC Edgar filings of energy companies.



</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.rollcall.com>Roll Call Online</A></FONT>



<BR><UL>

As election '96 winds down and this year's races become footnotes in annals of politics, the online service of Roll Call, the newspaper covering Capitol Hill since 1995 keeps tabs of Congress with news, hot policy briefings, commentary and more.  Stop in here to start preparing for the 1998 races.

</UL>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.fst.rdg.ac.uk/people/ajukesdj/l-eu-new.htm>EU Food Law News</A></FONT>



<BR>

<UL>Interested in the news about European regulations on organic livestock farming? Egg size grades?  Food additives used in flavorings?  From the Department of Food Science and Technology of the University of Reading, UK, feast on news about food law in the European Union.

</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.nela.org>National Employment Lawyers' Association</A></FONT>



<BR><UL>

Here's the Web office of NELA, the association founded in 1985 exclusively for lawyers representing employees in discrimination, termination, benefits and other employment-related matters.  NELA posts membership and affiliate information along with employment law news, updates, and info on its products and services.



</UL>

<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.tradezone.com/trdzone.htm>The Trade Zone</A></FONT>



<BR><UL>

For netizens and their lawyers engaged in international trade, here's a mall of links to useful sites for doing biz across the globe.  Follow pointers to banks, conventions, government offices, embassies, export resources, travel sites, trade publications, directories and reference materials, even world weather.

</UL>

</UL>



<UL>






<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of November 4th:</B></TT></B></font>

</P>

</UL>

</P>





</P>

<UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.primenet.com/~crh4/index.html>The World List: Non-U.S. Law-Related Resources for Internet Users</A></FONT>

<BR>

<UL>

Travel around the e-world with a big directory of links to legal and government sites for over 65 countries, from Argentina to Zambia. Brought to the Web by law professor Makoto Ibuski of Kaoshima University, Japan.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.lawandpolitics.com>Law & Politics Outta' Line</A></FONT>



<BR>

<UL>

Joining an ever-expanding pool of political sites this election year comes the opinionated online version of Minnesota's Journal of Law & Politics. Stop over for articles, good collections of legal and political links, and weekly offerings from "Cartoon Boy." 

</UL>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.doj/dea/deahome.html>Drug Enforcement Administration</A></FONT>



<BR>

<UL>

Meet the Department of Justice arm responsible for enforcing federal controlled substances laws and developing drug enforcement strategy and programs. The DEA, under administrator Thomas A. Constantine, posts congressional testimony, press releases, publications, even mug shots and information about drug fugitives.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.ddsi.com/banking>Ibanker: Internet Banking and Financial Index 

</A></FONT>



<BR>

<UL>

Banks are moving to cybertown in droves. Follow the links in this annotated directory to national and foreign banks, mortgage companies, banking and finance technology companies, and more.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.educom.edu/web/pubs/edupage.html>Edupage</A></FONT>



<BR>

<UL>

It's a technological world. Keep up with developments with regular summaries of technology news from Educom, "a Washington, D.C.-based consortium of leading colleges and universities seeking to transform education through the use of information technology."

</UL>



</UL>



