<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.fjc.gov/pubs.html>Federal Judicial Center Publications</A></FONT>

<UL><BR>

At the request of the Judicial Conference of the  United States, in 1967 Congress established the Federal  Judicial Center as the federal courts' agency for research and education. FJC posts (in Adobe format) a variety of publications on ADR, civil litigation, court administration, federal judicial history and much more.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.ins.lawnt.com>The Insurance Law List</A></FONT>

<UL>

</BR>Are you seeking a law firm experienced in representing insurance companies or self-insured corporations in the U.S., Canada or internationally? Do you specialize in insurance law and want to be listed?  Look into this searchable, interactive database of "over 5,500" insurance law firms.

</UL>







<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.adr.org/code.html>Code of Ethics for Commercial Arbitrators</A></FONT>

<UL>

<BR>What information should an arbitrator disclose to the parties? How may an arbitrator use confidential information? Is it proper for an arbitrator to suggest to the parties that they discuss settlement? Here are ethical guidelines for commercial arbitrators, prepared and approved by the ABA and the American Arbitration Association.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.rtl.org/supcourt.htm>Supreme Court Decisions on Abortion</A></FONT>

<UL>

<BR>Starting with the 1973 decision in Roe v. Wade, follow a chronology of summaries and selected full text opinions from the high court in abortion rights cases, presented  by Right to Life of Michigan.

</UL>





<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.kentlaw.edu/ulc>Drafts of Uniform and Model Acts</A></FONT>

<UL>

<BR>From the National Conference of Commissioners on Uniform  State Laws and Chicago-Kent College of Law browse a collection of drafts including Model Punitive Damages Act, Interstate Child Visitation Act, Uniform Unclaimed Property Act, revised U.C.C. articles 2 and 9.



</UL>















