<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.usdoj.gov/vawo>Violence Against Women Office</A></FONT>

<BR><UL>

In 1994, Congress passed the landmark Violence Against Women Act, instituting penalties and allocating resources for law enforcement in crimes against the majority gender. Visit the Web office responsible for focusing and coordinating Department of Justice efforts to combat violence against women.  Read press reports, testimony, crime  statistics and legislation.  With help and services  for victims.

</UL>



<P><FONT SIZE="+1"><A HREF=http://www.law.uc.edu/CCL/>The Center For Corporate Law</A></FONT>

