injury (SCI)?  If they're neurolawyers, plenty, according to the law

offices of Fick & Petty. A neurolawyer "must be knowledegable about the

biomechanics of neuroanatomy, neurophysiology, neurochemistry,

neuropsychology, neurorehabilitation . . . " And when they have any

spare time, they study the law.

</UL>

