</P>







<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of July 29:</B></TT></font> </P>

<P>

<B>

<a href="http://www.divorcenet.com/">Family Law Advisor</a>

</B>

<ul>



You don't have to be a family lawyer to represent clients who have family

law questions.  Embrace a wholesome collection of resources on marriage,

marital assets, paternity, divorce, custody and related topics.  Read the

Family Law Advisor e-zine. Thumb through an annotated divorce law

dictionary. And post questions on DivorceNet's bulletin boards.







</ul>

</P>

<P>





<a href="http://www.infolawalert.com/">

<B>Information Law Alert</B></a>

<ul>



Computers and information technology are transforming the legal landscape. 

Here to help cyberlawyers keep current is an e-zine covering encryption,

software patents, trademarks and domains, digital copying and related

topics. Editor Mark Voorhees invites visitors to e-mail their questions on

information law.



</ul>

</P>

<P>





<b>

<a href="http://www.law.ubc.ca/centres/crimjust.html">International Centre for Criminal Law Reform

and Criminal Justice Policy</a>

</b><ul>

On a mission "to improve the quality of justice through reform of criminal

law, policy and practice," the Vancouver-based International Centre,

founded in 1991, presents reports on subjects from aboriginal justice to

criminal procedure reform and new directions in sentencing.  Follow a link

to the Electronic Clearinghouse of the UN's Crime Prevention and Criminal

Justice Programme.



</ul>



</P>



<P>





<B>

 <a href="http://lcweb.loc.gov/">Library of Congress</a>

</B><ul>



Welcome to the new and improved Web site of the "the world's largest

repository of knowledge."  Established in 1800 as a legislative library,

the Library of Congress delivers to the Net its catalog, along with text,

images and offerings from exhibitions, the American Memory Historical

Collection, the THOMAS database of federal bills and other Congressional

information, reading rooms, electronic versions of many of its print

publications, and lots more.





</ul>

</P>

<P>

<B>

 <a href="http://www.ussc.gov/">United States Sentencing Commission</a>

</B>

<ul>

Created by the Sentencing Reform Act provisions of the Comprehensive Crime

Control Act of 1984, the U.S. Sentencing Commission is the independent

agency responsible for establishing federal court sentencing practices and

policies.  Visit the Commission's webspot for reports, guidelines, bylaws

of the National Association of Sentencing Commissions, training materials,

newsletters, even a job announcement or two.



</ul>

</P>





<P><FONT SIZE="+2" color="000000"><LI><TT><B>Week of July 22:</B></TT></font> </P>







<P>

<B>

<a href="http://www.afda.org/">Association of Federal Defense Attorneys</a>

</B>

<ul>







Is the defense bar under siege?  Fight back with the association devoted to

the interests of the federal defense bar.  If you represent defendants in

federal district and appellate courts, team up with the AFDA for news,

caselaw and legislation updates, sentencing guidelines info, events, links

and message boards.  (Some areas are restricted to members only.)



</UL>



</P>

<P>





<a href="http://www.courttv.com/">

<B>Court TV Law Center</B></a>

<ul>







Just in time for Court TV's fifth anniversary, the 24- hour-a-day,

seven-day-a-week cable network dedicated to reporting on the U.S. justice

system unwraps its redesigned, content-rich Web service.  The Law Center,

an affiliate of Counsel Connect Web, features news, information and

resources for all citizens, including the Small Business and Family Law

Centers, Legal Helpline, Lawyer Check, games, discussions, much more. 

Watch justice on the air  and on the Web.  Happy Anniversary Court TV.



</UL>



</P>

<P>





<b>

<a href="http://www.law.indiana.edu/glsj/vol1/aman.html">Indiana Journal of Global Legal Studies</a>

</b><ul>







Multinational corporations, global capital markets, rapidly advancing

technologies, major scientific discoveries.  Explore how "globalization"

affects the formulation of local, state, national and international law. 

Browse articles from Fall, 1993 to the current issue.





</UL>









</P>

<P>





<B>

 <a href="http://www.wco.com/~aerick/">Prisons and Prison Law</a>

</B>

<ul> 







Staff attorney Arnold Erikson of the private, not-for-profit legal services

group called the  Prison Law Office, invites you to "the other side of the

wall."  Focusing on California prisons, this site unlocks a roomful of

articles and information on crime and punishment. Read about prisoners'

rights, three strikes, habeas corpus, parole, death row, and related

topics.

</UL>



</P>





<P>





<B>

 <a href="http://www.securitieslaw.com/">Securities Fraud and Investor Protection</a>

</B><ul>







The stock market has seen a lot of action this summer, most of it lawful. 

Suspect fraudulent conduct?  Securities  lawyer Harry S. Miller has

compiled a lay-person's  and non-securities lawyers' guide to investor's

rights and stockbroker duties, incluidng topics such  as broker/customer

disputes, calculation of damages  and securities arbitration.   Don't play

the market  without it.



</UL>



