<P><b><a href="http://www.brook.edu/FP/PROJECTS/NUCWCOST/WEAPONS.HTM">Nuclear

Weapons Cost Study Project</a></b>

<ul>

Since the government began work on atomic weapons development in 1940, the U.S.

has spent about four trillion dollars on its nuclear arsenal.  After the Cold

War, the U.S. continues nuclear weapons spending. From the Manhattan Project to

present day active nuclear facilities, this "atomic audit" from the W. Alton

Jones Foundation details the costs of building, delivering, commanding, as well

as defending against, nuclear bombs.

</ul>





