Legal Times.  They appear in the following order:  attorney,
employment, support staff.<P>

ERISA/EMPLOYEE BENEFITS<BR>
Washington, D.C. boutique law firm specializing in employee
benefits seeks a recent graduate.  Excellent credentials and
superior writing skills required.  Please send cover letter and
resume to: 1625 Massachusetts Ave., N.W., Suite 450, Washington,
D.C. 20036, Attn: Darlene Lassiter.<P>

ATTORNEY<BR>
Position with national consulting firm providing intellectual
property services to corporations and law firms.  One to three
years of experience, excellent verbal and written communication
skills.  Patent bar registration required.  Please send resume and
salary history to: TechLaw, Inc., 14500 Avion Parkway, Suite 300,
Chantilly, VA  20151-1101, Attn: IP.  NO PHONE CALLS.  EEO.<P>

ASSISTANT CITY ATTORNEY<BR>
City of Alexandria, Virginia, seeking an attorney to join the City
Attorney's Office.  Applicants should have:  (1) sound academic
credentials; (2) experience or demonstrated knowledge in one or
more of areas of local government law; and (3) experience or
demonstrated competency in conducting civil litigation.  This
position affords significant client agency responsibility and an
excellent professional working environment in Old Town. Obtain
application form from Personnel Office, P.O. Box 178, Alexandria,
Virginia 22313, (703) 838-4422.<BR>
EEO/AA<P>

TRADEMARK ATTORNEY<BR>
Mid-size D.C. law firm has an immediate opening for a mid-level
associate to join our consumer products oriented trademark,
copyright and advertising practice.  The firm requires an
associate with 2-4 years' experience who is comfortable with
advising clients regarding proposed advertising, including
trademark clearances in the U.S. and internationally.  The right
candidate will have direct client contact in a position which will
confer substantial responsibility.  A strong, concise and clear
writing style is a must.  Litigation expertise helpful but not
required.  Please send resume to Tucker, Flyer & Lewis, 1615 L
Street, N.W., Suite 400, Washington, D.C. 20036.  Attention:
Recruitment Coordinator (Trademark).<P>

