ASSISTANT GENERAL COUNSEL<BR>
(0930-96-KD-LT)<BR>
Civil Litigation<BR>
The Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority (WMATA) is an
Interstate Compact Agency engaged in the construction and
operation of a rapid rail and bus system in the National Capital
Area.  The Office of General Counsel requires an attorney to
assume responsibility for personal injury and associated types of
litigation in state and federal courts.  The attorney selected
will be responsible for pretrial, trial and appellate
representation in both routine and complex litigation.  The
anticipated compensation range for this position is approximately
$45,972 - $60,000 depending upon experience and qualifications.
The successful candidate will have:<BR><BR>
A J.D. or L.L.B. degree and D.C. Bar membership required.
Applicants must also be admitted to practice law or gain admission
to practice within one (1) year, in all federal, state and local
courts of Maryland or Virginia.<BR><BR>
Demonstrated working knowledge of personal injury law.
Previous litigation experience at the trial court level,
preferably involving third party liability issues, and highly
developed skills in legal analysis, oral and written advocacy
skills are essential.<BR><BR>
Jury trial experience and experience at the appellate level are
desired.<BR><BR>
WMATA provides an extensive benefits package and a non-smoking
work environment.  Applications/resumes including title and
position number, salary history, writing sample and salary
requirements must be received by JANUARY 17, 1997.  Submit to:<BR>
WASHINGTON METROPOLITAN AREA TRANSIT AUTHORITY<BR>
OFFICE OF HUMAN RESOURCE<BR>
MANAGEMENT AND PLANNING<BR>
600 FIFTH STREET, N.W.<BR>
WASHINGTON, D.C.  20001<BR>
