<TITLE>Counsel Quote's Media Inquiries</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"  LINK="#000080" VLINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="/counselquote/paper.gif">

<CENTER><IMG SRC="/counselquote/queriesheader.gif" ALT="Counsel Quote Media Queries" ALIGN=TOP></CENTER>

<HR>
<center><A HREF="/images/cquotenavbar.map"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/counselquote/cquotenavbar.gif" ISMAP></A></center>
<HR>
<blockquote>
<P>
This is the place to start when you need legal sources with particular
expertise and anecdotes -- they're out there somewhere, and Counsel Quote can find them
for you.</P>
<P>
If you are a working journalist or author, submit the following form and we'll post your
request -- with your name, e-mail address and phone number -- in a special forum on Counsel
Connect. Our members check this forum frequently and will get back to
you if they think they've got expertise you can use.</P>

<P><I>One note</I>: Counsel Connect has 35,000 members, all of whom have
access to the Media Inquiries forum. Cast your request generally enough
that your competition won't know what enterprise piece you're working
on.</P> 

<B>For example, don't say:</B>
<UL><I>I need a lawyer who can discuss whether Lilly White
Restaurants Inc. botched its response to discrimination
complaints.</I></UL>
<B>Instead say:</B>
<UL><I>I'm looking for a lawyer who can discuss
discrimination from a defense perspective.</I></UL>

<I>One more note</I>: <B>This service is only open to reporters or authors.</B> If
you're looking for someone to represent you,  use <A
HREF="/lawyersearch/">Lawyer Search</A> or <A HREF="/qrfp/">Quick
Request for Proposals</A>.

</blockquote>
