<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Counsel Quote -  Counsel Canvass</TITLE>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="paper.gif">
<p align=center><img src="/counselquote/canvasheader.gif" width=600 height=100 alt="COUNSEL CANVAS"></P>
<HR>
<center><A HREF="/images/cquotenavbar.map"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/counselquote/cquotenavbar.gif" ISMAP></A></center>
<HR>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Counsel Connect is a private online community for lawyers, which means it's
the perfect place for you to poll lawyers on particular news issues. For
example, you're writing a story on Dr. Jack Kevorkian and assisted suicide.
Wouldn't it be interesting to learn whether lawyers would convict or acquit
Kevorkian under Michigan's assisted suicide law? Another example. Your
story's on Paula Jones' sexual harassment suit against President Clinton.
Why not ask lawyers whether the president should be required to go to trial
during his presidential term? You get the picture. And you can canvass 
counsel here. </P>

<P>We'll promote your survey online, and send you results when the survey is
complete.</P>

<P>A few caveats before you dive in. First, like traditional surveys, the best
online surveys take time. Please realize that the tighter your deadline,
the fewer responses you'll get. Ideally, we run surveys for a month before
analyzing the results. </P>

<P>Second, consider that these surveys aren't conducted scientifically.
Responses come, not from a random sample of members, but from members who
choose to go to a particular area of the system, and choose to fill out a
particular survey. Since surveys are anonymous, individuals may vote
multiple times. And, while the overwhelming majority of Counsel Connect
members are attorneys, some non-attorney legal professionals, such as law
librarians, belong to Counsel Connect and may fill out these surveys. So
while you'll get a picture of where the legal community stands on a
particular topic, take our survey method into account when you report our
survey results. </P>

<P>Third, Counsel Connect reserves the right to reject any survey submitted to
us for any reason at all. We can't guarantee we'll run your survey, but
we'll make sure to let you know if we can't. </P>

<P>Finally, if you use our survey results in any way, please attribute the
information to Counsel Connect.</P>

<a href="surveyform.html"><B><I>Submit a Survey Topic to Counsel Connect</I></B></a>


<H4>Examples:</H4>
<P>We also regularly survey our members on some of the important issues
lawyers discuss on Counsel Connect. You may want to incorporate some of our
survey results into your stories. Here are some of our past online polls:</P>

<P><a href="survey3.html"><I>A Fine Line: Ethics and Morals</I></a></P>

<P><a href="survey2.html"><I>Grappling With the Right to Die</I></a></P>

<P><a href="survey1.html"><I>Sexual Harassment: Would You Know it if You Saw it?</I></a></P>

<P>If you have questions about Counsel Connect's surveys, please send e-mail
to <a href="mailto:deirdre.terry@counsel.com">deirdre.terry@counsel.com</a>. </P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>


</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
