<A NAME="tab"><TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>  
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="west.html">Go West and Grow . . .</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>From the Counsel Connect Hot Docs Library, read U.S. District Court Judge Paul L. Friedman's rejection of a merger settlement between West Publishing Co./Thomson Publishing, Inc. and state and federal regulators. Friedman found the decree "in the public interest, but for one provision" -- the page number licensing:  "The court suggests that the public interest would be served if West and Thomson would agree to amend the license provision in the proposed final judgment's [pagination license] to provide a free license to all who request one until West's copyright claim is judicially resolved once and for all." <P></FONT>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/west.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/aloha.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400> 
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="aloha.html">Aloha to Gay Marriage?</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>From the Counsel Connect Library, read the full text of a Hawaiian Circuit Court judge's ruling that the state failed to show any compelling reason for denying marriage licenses to same-sex couples. An appeal to the state's Supreme Court has been filed, so a final ruling on the issue will not be made until next year.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<A NAME="tab"><TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400> 
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="king.html">Who Owns The Dream?</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>[Editor's Note: The estate of slain civil rights leader Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. sued CBS for violation of the estate's copyright on the historic "I Have A Dream" speech. Dr. King delivered the the speech to a crowd of 200,000 in August 1963, and, according to the complaint, registered three different versions of the speech with the U.S. Copyright Office. The King estate alleges that a videotape on the civil rights movement produced and distributed by CBS, which includes footage of most of Dr. King's speech, violates their copyright. Here is the complaint from the Counsel Connect Hot Docs Library.<P></FONT>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/mlk.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>



<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/adm.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400> 
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="adm.html">ADM's $100 Million Plea</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>From the Counsel Connect Library, read the full text of ADM's record breaking plea agreement. The deal the agribusiness giant cut with the DOJ settles criminal price-fixing charges against the corporation, but leaves some top executives exposed.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<A NAME="tab"><TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400> 
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="fox.html">"Squishing Rupert Like A Bug"</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>That's what Ted Turner is looking forward to, according to Fox News Network's antitrust suit challenging the merger of Time Warner and Turner Broadcasting System. Here is Fox's complaint from the Counsel Connect Hot Docs Library.<P></FONT>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/fox.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/perot2.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="perot.html">Perot Fights Debate Snub</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>From the Counsel Connect Library, read the full text of Ross Perot's appeal in his fight to be included in the '96 presidential debates. Other election-related Library documents available to Counsel Connect members include: the Federal Election Commission's suits against the Christian Coalition and Gopac for illegally funding Republican candidates, including Newt Gingrich; the Dole campaign's allegations that some of President Bill Clinton's staffers used White House facilities for campaign work; and the FCC ruling on free network air time for presidential candidates.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<A NAME="tab"><TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="fuhrman.html">Perjury Plea for Former Detective</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>At O.J. Simpson's criminal trial, then-Detective Mark Fuhrman testified that he had not used a racial slur in the past ten years. The State of California then prosecuted Fuhrman for perjury, and negotiated a plea bargain that allowed the former detective to plead no contest, avoid serving time, and pay a minimum fine. Here is the full text of the agreement, straight from the Hot Docs section of Counsel Connect's library.</FONT>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/fuhrman.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4></A>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/marlboro.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400> 
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/marlboro.html">Marlboro Man versus Marlboro</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>The widow of the "Marlboro Man" has sued the tobacco industry, alleging that its fraud and deceit contributed to David McLean's death from lung cancer. McLean was featured in a long-running campaign for Philip Morris' most popular brand of cigarettes. McLean's widow alleges that he routinely smoked as many as five packs of cigarettes a day in the course of shooting print and television commercials.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/pepsi.html">Pepsi Contest Goes Flat</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>John Leonard is suing Pepsico for failing to provide the Harrier jet he attempted to purchase in the soft drink company's "Pepsi Stuff" ad campaign. According to advertisements, Pepsi Points were available for ten cents each. One advertisement offered a Harrier jet for 7,000,000 Pepsi Points. Mr. Leonard submitted 15 Pepsi Points and a check for $700,008.50 to purchase the balance of Pepsi Points required for the jet.</FONT>
</TD>
 
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=89 SRC="/images/spotlight/pepsi.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER WIDTH=120> 
<IMG WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 SRC="/images/spotlight/diver.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/games/">Seminar: Summer in Atlanta</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>As the Games unfold, jump into a seminar on 100 years of sports law. For the weeks spanning the Olympics, sports lawyers, experts and fans on Counsel Connect discuss amateur sports law. Listen in and post your own comments and questions.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400> 
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/caldera.html">Take 2: Microsoft Antitrust</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>Utah software maker Caldera, Inc. is attempting "to finish what the Justice Department couldn't" -- the company is suing Microsoft for antitrust violations. Caldera alleges that the behemoth Microsoft has monopolized the DOS market by practicing illegal tying, exclusive dealing and by tortiously interfering with economic relations.</FONT>
</TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=120 BGCOLOR=FFFFFF>
<IMG WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=80 SRC="/images/spotlight/dos2.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=120>
<IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=90 SRC="/images/spotlight/bomb9.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/mcveigh2.html">Watching From Oklahoma</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>Over defendants' objections, victims' families in Oklahoma will have access to closed  circuit TV coverage of the Denver trial of Timothy McVeigh and Terry Nichols. Read the oral argument and ruling.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
 

<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/hagen.html">Hagen v. AOL</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>Has America Online, the world's largest online service, been conveniently rounding up its "Online Clock" at users' expense? Apparently so -- the monmouth provider has agreed to settle a class-action lawsuit for $2,750,000 by providing free connect time for users. The Stipulation of Settlement follows.</FONT>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG WIDTH=70 HEIGHT=70 BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/aol.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
 

<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=110 BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/whitehouse.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400> 
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/white/">The Special Committee's Whitewater Report</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>The Special Committee to Investigate Whitewater released its reports to the public on June 18 -- 759 pages from the <A HREF="/spotlight/white/">Republicans</A>, and almost 400 pages from the <A HREF="/spotlight/white2/">Democrats</A>. The documents have generated reams of news articles and commentary -- now you can read them yourself and judge whether the majority opinion is just a political smear or raises legitimate questions about the President and First Lady.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/bakke.html">Backing Off Bakke?</A></B></FONT><BR>
The U.S. Supreme Court stunned affirmative action advocates by declining to review Texas v. Hopwood, the 5th Circuit's ruling that Texas Law School's ethnic diversity-based admissions program was unconstitutional. Read the petition for certiorari and the Court's decision.
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=LEFT> 
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/scales10.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER> 
<IMG WIDTH=70 HEIGHT=90 BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/boggs.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/boggs.html">Virtual Power Lunch: Thomas Hale Boggs Jr.</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>Thomas Hale Boggs Jr. is one of the most prominent lobbyists in the country. No stranger to the halls of power, he is the son of two members of Congress. Boggs is online on Counsel Connect discussing the role he's played as lobbyist in Washington, D.C., during the last 30 years. Here he is discussing the usefulness of lobbying.</FONT><P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/cda/">Seminar- Communications Decency Act Ruling</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>Calling the Internet "a never-ending world-wide conversation" which "deserves the highest protection from governmental intrusion," a federal three-judge panel ruled that the Communications Decency Act is unconstitutional. Here's our attorney seminar about the ruling, re-published from Counsel Connect.</FONT>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=LEFT> 
<IMG WIDTH=73 HEIGHT=92 BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/comp.gif"> 
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
 

<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=114 BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/bio.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/fund.html">Superfund Trashed?</A></B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>Are businesses that dump hazardous waste responsible for cleaning up dump sites created prior 1980, the year CERCLA (popularly called Superfund) took effect?  Contrary to law in other circuits, a federal judge in Alabama dismissed a CERCLA consent decree finding Superfund is <I>not</I> retroactive.</FONT>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/dole.html">Dole Attacks the A.B.A.</A></B></FONT><BR>
Presidential nominee Bob Dole recently spoke to the American Society of Newspaper Editors in Washington D.C. where he lashed out against not only President Clinton, but a number of Federal Judges and the American Bar Association as well.
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/dole.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG WIDTH=82 HEIGHT=97 BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/scien2.gif">
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B><A HREF="/spotlight/scien2.html">Making Law, Making Enemies</A></B></FONT><BR>
Reprinted from <I>The American Lawyer</I>, this article examines The Church of Scientology's  numerous clashes with the online community. The church maintains it is trying to protect its <I>copyrighted</I> religious dogma, but netizens everywhere insist it is out to silence its critics -- under the guise of copyright protection.
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=520 CELLPADDING=6 CELLSPACING=4>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=400>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>Tobacco and the FDA</FONT></B><BR>
<FONT SIZE=-0>Here's <A HREF="/spotlight/bandw.html"><B>Brown & Williamson's summary</B></A> of the tobacco companies' arguments against the FDA's proposed regulation of nicotine as a drug. B&W argues that tobacco is an "agricultural commodity" and compares it to "frozen orange juice or applesauce." Spotlight has also acquired the tobacco companies' <A HREF="/spotlight/tobacco/contents.htm"><B>entire 2,000 page report</B></A>, which voraciously dissects and attacks every argument the FDA has made.</FONT>
</TD>

<TD WIDTH=120 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG WIDTH=80 HEIGHT=130 BORDER=0 SRC="/images/spotlight/smoking.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


